here it was in better or worse condition and where signs of leakage could be found. He didn’t push to sell us anything and even suggested we’d be fine for a couple more years with what we had. Ultimately we decided that we were in a good position to replace our roof and gutters this year. Zoom clearly informed us about all of our options and was straightforward about things we probably did not need, especially on our smaller home. He was transparent with costs and the final price was extremely competitive for our area. Scheduling was easy. The roofers were accommodating and were careful with our driveway and yard. They used excellent quality shingles. Within a couple days we had several neighbors asking who did our great-looking new roof.\n\nIn short, I definitely recommend these guys. Zoom goes above and beyond with communication, which really helps to make a large, stressful purchase much easier.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0YYHtEaLQNbfJVFxwQ7KNJm_jEuiprz_bo8PZBSF0T9RBIfbp_DsgE5Ut6ASho3_DtGO5xSZGwm9tPRLOWE_t3cNK70LQMtQINhnSMNFtjKlFgbg8wZ-Bki3nDHID6L5uuBP9bem9d2jN8=k-no"],"When":"2025-8-26"},{"Name":"Huda Tillisy","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXTsVSCQfiiD3j8n8QydVva3FbnS6gWlzfg6bkKZ-x5mV2hTlA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Zoom helped my family get our roof replaced by insurance and registered our roof for a 50 year warranty. He even paid for our skylight replacement when insurance refused to cover that. We had a leak coming through the ceiling and Zoom replaced the drywall once the roof was replaced. Insurance covered everything including repainting the entire interior of the house. Zoom and the other owner, Jesse, knew how to handle the claim process and took care of everything for us. We are very happy with Greenlake Roofing and would recommend them to our friends and family.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0QSb9OMmAhr4JuR_HFTObWCoUTNsaPhjp5A8EEOedQAIdoEu3