roughout the job. we really appreciated how smooth and stress-free they made the whole process. i'd definitely recommend them to anyone needing roof work done at a fair price.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Chase Case","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ2Rpvo9FrHmZ5EdfHSQQTNdAem8YysNcZdsPk0E_TSfpxmlg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Here’s the revised and contextually expanded review, following your requirements: It’s raining heavily in Seattle right now, and just a week ago I would have been worried about my roof leaking. Thankfully, since hiring Andrew \u0026 Sons Roof Repair, I can relax knowing my home is protected from the rain. We had struggled for months with different roofers trying to fix our leaks, but nothing seemed to work until we called them. Elias came out quickly to give us an estimate, which was very fair and straightforward. The crew showed up on time every day, worked efficiently, and were always polite and respectful. They kept everything tidy and made sure to clean up thoroughly at the end of each day—my neighbors even noticed how neat the work area was. With a young child at home, I really appreciated how safe and considerate Raymond and the team were around our property. The job was finished right on schedule and the workmanship was excellent. After they completed the roof repair, Elias returned to double-check that everything was sealed properly and that there were no more issues with water getting in. We also had them replace a gutter and install gutter guards on the back of the house. Everything was completed on time, at a reasonable price, and with no pressure to add unnecessary services. I am truly impressed with the professionalism and quality of their work. If you need roofing help in Seattle, I highly recommend calling them!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sophie Hogan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUxgToNVF_Y5faDNaTNqtlPDIYwx9GOK1ixuKEnlw9lhht1gR0=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Over the past several years, I’ve had Andrew \u0026 Sons Roof Repair handle two complete roof replacements at different homes in Seattle, both times after considering multiple bids. I’m happy to recommend them as a great example of what good customer service and excellent roofing work should look like. After two outstanding experiences, I wouldn’t think of going anywhere else for my roofing needs. Most recently, Elias helped guide me through the process. He was knowledgeable, never pushy, and kept me updated throughout the whole project. I had a complicated roof ventilation issue, and Elias suggested smart solutions that I hadn’t seen before, even with my background as a retired general contractor. The crew worked efficiently and paid close attention to the details on my tricky roof, making sure everything was handled properly. Their team also installed seamless gutters that were done with top quality workmanship. When the job was finished, the cleanup was thorough and the property looked great. As someone who’s spent years in construction and tends to be very detail-focused, I can say I was truly satisfied with the final result. It’s a relief to have such a positive experience from start to finish.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jeff Evans","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKq4RCSBfMrH7EZ81gAkNC06cRyC9cqwk--yFbsYkPd5v8GuA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had a great experience working with this roofing team in Seattle. Our roof is pretty complicated and had leaks in two different spots. When I contacted them, they were very professional and quickly set up an appointment. They used a drone to find the problems—one spot had missing shingles and another area had an issue with the gutter. They gave us several repair options and clear estimates, including a partial repair or a full roof replacement with a warranty. What really stood out was that they tarped the leaking areas right away, which none of the other roofers offered. This gave us the time we needed to make a decision, and there was no pressure to choose the most expensive option. We decided to go with the partial repair. They stuck to the agreement and finished the work on both problem areas in just a couple of days. Elias, the crew supervisor, was very skilled and easy to work with. One leak was fixed right away, and when the spot near the gutter needed more attention, Elias sent his crew back out promptly after I called. Overall, I’m very impressed with their prompt service, honesty, and straightforward approach. I would definitely recommend them to anyone looking for roofing services in Seattle. They were much better than other companies I contacted, who were either too busy or just wanted to push for a full roof replacement.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"J Bowen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjViQVgoMtdEHtkc2-C8qLokvb9jElFMIjWjAwH0z3fqjbxNXqc=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"From my very first call to the roofing team in Seattle, the experience was outstanding. Elias helped me get started over the phone, and Raymond came out to give a thorough estimate. The crew that installed the new asphalt shingles was skilled and professional, and the whole process—from start to final walk-through and warranty handoff with Raymond—was smooth and efficient. What really set them apart was the personal attention and care. You just don’t get that kind of service with the bigger roofing companies. The shingles they used were great quality, and their installation standards went above and beyond what’s typical in the area. Everything was completed quickly and efficiently, and my new roof looks fantastic. The whole process, from first contact to receiving my warranty, was done in about two weeks. I couldn’t be happier with the service and the results. Highly recommend this roofing company to anyone in Seattle!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Carolyn Colon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKShOdieakL72_eKldPExHDqY6IaDCMkK40DtrUJKGrTnGNnw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The team was very quick to respond to our inquiries. Elias came out to our home in Seattle and walked us through different roofing and gutter options. He was very professional, friendly, and knew a lot about roof repairs and materials. He took the time to answer all our questions and made sure we understood each option. The quality of materials offered and the workmanship promised were both impressive. Their discounts and pricing were explained clearly, and we appreciated the straightforward approach. Overall, we felt well taken care of and would definitely recommend them to anyone in the Seattle area looking for reliable roofing services.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Courtney Decker","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIPqC9-D5pH55OqT8iZbbLfLF-PqyntcgpKAcMFtn_j0Z1vdA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I received a great quote for a high-quality roofing job, including replacing my old cinder block chimney with a brick one and installing new shingles across my entire roof. Throughout the process, Elias was honest and clear, only recommending work that was truly necessary. The whole experience was excellent from start to finish. Communication was frequent, with regular updates about scheduling since the Seattle weather can be unpredictable. The team completed the chimney and roofing work efficiently, finishing the main projects in just two days and taking another half day to clean up and remove all debris. I would definitely recommend this roofing company to anyone in need of reliable and professional service in the Seattle area.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"layla collier","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL4iflW8c3E6iI6ygXZ36RLU7nIouW63fx2tyzsNtmisBnruQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I was referred to this roofing company by a co-worker, and from the moment Elias arrived, he took care of everything for us. He made sure our insurance claim went smoothly and handled the roof inspection with attention to detail. Elias even came by on a Saturday so we could choose our shingle color, which made the process really convenient. His communication throughout the project was excellent, and we always felt informed every step of the way. The roofing crew was quick and efficient, but they also made sure the work was high quality. They cleaned up thoroughly, so it looked like they were never there. I highly recommend this company in Seattle for anyone needing roof repair or replacement after storm damage.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
