hael","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJFHg4Bl_3xyLFTnr2pmbwfhFzCh8GD_lCuu8yJxNehPhkwPcTR=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Well, I have to say this relationship started off well with Travis Hendrickson at Four Seasons. Got a quick bid, and for a 3,000 SF home it cost $14,000 which was the middle bid. He uses GAF Timberline and replaced two skylights. We had an externally baffled roof installed. The roof is good that's why this isn't a 1-star review. My issue with Travis is that there is no follow up after 2 months of attempts to get him to put things back to how they were. The chandelier cap was knocked loose from all the banging on the roof. I'd replace it myself, but I dont have a ladder that tall. A gutter also got kicked loose, and he said he would come back and re-attached and now it's been almost 3 months, and he hasn't come by to finish it up. His crew also left a mess everywhere. I had shingles, loose nails, and tons of debris all over the floor where they installed the skylight. No follow through on making sure the job is fully complete. These are just basic customer service items too. I cleaned up the debris myself, but don't have the high ladders like he does to reconnect the other stuff.\n\n[Update 4/25/17]\n\nFinally sent a guy out to reconnect the gutter, but no help on the chandelier.\n\n[Update 4/15/20]\n\nHe actually came out for a warranty check. It would have been nice to get a notice from him that he'd be coming by. Adding back a star as he did take a proper look to see if the roof was the source of the leak we're having.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn00iH0MWEYy27QXtxU5Sp7e7lB1mGs9UeHB_PR4fp_T-JnniqRATC6iFRHoVNmV_LpFylaAXw_D4PHpROmChoFjndXd6Oi5alRdfJUMYUyM56Dv-Js4G0LUPO4udOA4PrsofIrv=k-no"],"When":"2017-4-20"},{"Name":"carol osborn","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIxQ1Z4fA-vGIhblW4ZU1aTGnimRKNcHVfm0xvoGGo75Yw-xw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Just had roof replacement and gutters done.  Great job on installing and they were on time and cleaned everything up and easy to work with.  Thank you Terry, Vance, Tiana,  Travis and all the crew.  Looks great!!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Fedor Torchilo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKPdxriGKUo2qBh6dSG15pcu_oT2js6Kko_Pu3lkiw-ojb0iw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Work was done quickly so that's good. Quality seems okay although the rainy season hasn't really started. But had issues with the initial estimate and a lot of upcharges after the fact a lot of which should have been disclosed up front after the walk through. Also was told there would be a follow up regarding some questions on the work done and a bent gutter none of which ever happened. Overall I would steer clear there are plenty of other solid companies.\n\n*edit had the 4 seasons team follow up they were understanding of the whole situation. sent some folks out to fix the few dents and answered the questions I had they also credited back some money related to some external fascia. Overall I appreciate the genuine care they have for their reputation and really seems like they care about the customer.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Linh Du","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK3Qa7gXgxmJf_bKS4gTYrjJSV7pySnQ5rimipN-iATU6jRBQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Excellent company!  Travis gave me a good bid and he was able to accommodate my needs and fitted me in the schedule that I requested for my new roof installation. Greg, Alex, Luis, and Justin were very profession and did quality work.  I have great satisfaction in Four Seasons Roofing. I highly recommend this company!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Trudy Lothyan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL7d5ZF1nVJM6J93t8RcuaATn2Hpvc6MgjE2DtHq7XEC_QqQA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Four Seasons Roofing was recommended to us by our insurance company  after we had a catastrophic  roof leak. The original roofing company refused to honor their warranty and Four Seasons worked us into their schedule very promptly.  Their roofers were great to work with, very pleasant, cleaned up after themselves and kept us apprised  of their progress. We highly recommend them.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Growth Pointe","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUHucey3ELbl9KDlJ0Jkst6FZeYOKrdFKzcOrlOS5GKq7mnlfiB=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The folks at Four Seasons Roofing did an outstanding job on a significant roof and ceiling drywall repair at my home in Edmonds. They were timely, dependable, friendly, courteous and professional. All aspects of the job were handled well to ensure that the job was completed to my satisfaction. I would definitely hire Travis and his team again! Each of them did a terrific job! 🌟🌟🌟🌟🌟","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
