-s/APNQkAEQCGfOCKFKv3vw8jvCzXRYPQvTIC3dv6ceUxnc6Sh25_LdD3vqZabPEkBntWtVI72SksNw89hAZaKkxSRBD543d4uWbYUELBsvo4E0kw89a_gQF8Zqih4eYzjzRDyrlYrjFtHSeTPYVuk=w529-h298-k-no"},{"title":"House","image":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/gps-cs-s/APNQkAHfizzlwtk83DXFlfEwDxydjdhCy4msERRkYS0YHCqxZwbjLB396lFjgbWS-6uRQHE_sqQyVuR14ok0TBQ_SiWg3r-3bkTAG2xgNyws6QBMK801Kv7b6faNplpSYHvVBIXuBAFepQ=w535-h298-k-no"},{"title":"By owner","image":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/gps-cs-s/APNQkAGWfW-RWxa2v20-E3eiaV3Khz-aRqcuQMzLbMe5FdW085l7FnbckexSOF92o3mM4fh8o6TPa6Nl6NKu_Nd9TsMtx9PuD1qoCZ4PeIGW9--_plUUXIkFC8xvJNLSdpHGMKGCLF5u0PZj1fo=w529-h298-k-no"},{"title":"Street View \u0026 360°","image":"https://streetviewpixels-pa.googleapis.com/v1/thumbnail?panoid=OsoWezTXchda6kFQbWuelA\u0026cb_client=maps_sv.tactile.gps\u0026w=224\u0026h=298\u0026yaw=191.76411\u0026pitch=0\u0026thumbfov=100"}],"reservations":null,"order_online":[{"link":"https://www.threetreeroofing.com/contact-three-tree-roofing/three-tree-roofing-seattle-company-office/","source":"threetreeroofing.com"}],"menu":{"link":"","source":""},"owner":{"id":"104744806295804962801","name":"Three Tree Roofing (Owner)","link":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104744806295804962801"},"complete_address":{"borough":"West Woodland","street":"1455 NW Leary Wy","city":"Seattle","postal_code":"98107","state":"Washington","country":"US"},"about":[{"id":"service_options","name":"Service options","options":[{"name":"Onsite services","enabled":true}]},{"id":"accessibility","name":"Accessibility","options":[{"name":"Wheelchair accessible restroom","enabled":true}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Wolf Rendall","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjULOajxXy8EEsa-_o-f5yMLrMpRKDDTmpqTLa3LZIkLTs_jk6Uk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great service, they went above and beyond and led with a strong price for high quality materials and modern techniques for vents and skylights. I had them replace my 20 year old roof for my home in Wallingford and they were careful not to harm our driveway with heavy machinery and cleanup of the site was good. I added on a gutter replacement and feel great about all the work done. Schedule was flexible and follow-up was prompt. Special thanks to Caleb, Dino, Kyle, and their crews.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn14f8EkqE89S7y_renf3IHXXFssBOciWRRAh-sowfSwIxHX69rzcoptNXiWg8OsdtkKC-crucl08W22mPSKEFvgipspC95sKRoXzzlMGfRdIK1XLvaWAdeBWHiLcRuSneaqItGmMAa3otkD=k-no"],"When":"2025-10-27"},{"Name":"Darlene Gwaltney","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJdR9BMQhMscY4dHr6eUlqQ8XytlhMb7uzprlYCcnOo4uxEdQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I got bids from three roofing companies last year since we knew this was one of the priority projects for our new home and Three Tree was an easy choice. Chase came out and provided an assessment, was able to apply a quick patch to an area that was compromised, and got back quickly with a quote and no pressure on timing. I also felt very comfortable that they could navigate our three story house that has issues around access for trucks or cranes.\n\nI let Chase know we were planning to use them, but timing would be a bit farther out than originally discussed. When I reached back out 8 months after our original meeting I anticipated having to haggle over the quote, but they kept the original price we discussed and got us on the calendar. When another job was delayed, they were able to move us up to a faster start date that worked for everyone.\n\nThe crew was lovely, punctual, and super attentive to detail for the cleanup process. They were efficient in their work, and even with a few minor repairs that were needed in one section of the roof, and two bump outs they were finished in two days.\n\nWe look forward to not needing another roof replacement, but would definitely recommend this team to our family, friends, or neighbors.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1zfyefOZ_QoR63phbiIqBH7B-YlfYO2meVsnlq8lDxA25zvr0FQTcTSSJWgGKGrq6q5d4c3UlL6nZDKnYcBkGV2iWq9AjJ_2pY5F4kq6gxBCA4S8569I0YmY0f9pnAzpNDozc0=k-no"],"When":"2025-4-22"},{"Name":"Briana W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJtNV1ORaB6mcUQqgPHTDjDu_wsVt3SzrcRVx4c6afZRrrKoA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My roof and gutter replacement were completed with Three Tree Roofing in April 2025.  I am so completely pleased with my experience with Three Tree I wish I could give more stars!  Start to finish I cannot find one thing I would change.\n\nThe estimate provided by Danny was thorough and well explained.  The price was slightly more than another company I got an estimate from, but for the top-of-the-line CertainTeed NorthGate rubberized shingles, a far superior product with 50yr warranty!  It was an easy decision to go with Three Tree.\n\nJake was my PM, and he explained the process to me and allowed me the flexibility to schedule gutter install after my house was painted.  He kept me posted on schedule delays for rain and when we were ready to get started.\n\nThe roofing crew showed up on time and worked like a well-oiled machine!  Edwin was a great foreman, and the crew was definitely experienced.  The vents and pipes that penetrate the roof were all replaced or coated to match the roofing, so they look new and seamless.  The work area and yard were also left clean.\n\nAfter painting wrapped up the gutters were custom-made onsite and installed.  The gutter covers (perforated leaf guards) match the gutter color.  The full assembly is high quality and installed perfectly.\n\nOur roof looks AMAZING.  We have gotten so many compliments already.  I highly recommend calling Three Tree Roofing for your roofing project.  I cannot thank this company and their team enough for doing everything RIGHT and making this an enjoyable process.\n\n(Before/after photos provided)","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1Pl1lZubPl1h7-BLFRGVZ6qTyvxHNPUcmIbuCT5iLYI0ZjuOqnbFjZEYqwqfuA24lwxwL7H_l_bhiJ__mXEBfKJsMpCytGhKFvPcc9rkOMwIo5fxQa7fw2RcRY2l6r9ZqoJb6n=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1NSs35wO-8cg2YKFgvGwGeskACTctMg3hlO0q8ltBSWdMga3u6Kz1DEFD0YK-6F4A-97jqBWz1vbHcsH0FvA0d8VI8ULD7IMb9AASRlRXgAheZufuNi8hbyF58K-WMkITbCklR_Q=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2qwH49wIPVnc0x-xFbbxR1FfNM6-LaeV2aL1l41CqMFTMXL_X-uMPQlLxn_o9uf1cIAmwzVriAAfQIqx0P1cmgMRiEQTxD8kplOrOcKQhUOzofBrHx8cOPm1emdNeeHNR6NNK3=k-no"],"When":"2025-5-2"},{"Name":"Pradnyesh Patil","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVF51l-HyKZ3cp3yqQM5wB3e00NgwTfgwyDUWXSz1zV6aIRRwwhWA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently hired Three Tree Roofing to replace my roof, and I couldn’t be happier with the results. From start to finish, their team was professional, punctual, and incredibly thorough.\nThey communicated clearly throughout the process, explained all my options, and kept me updated every step of the way.\n\nThe workmanship is great—the roof looks fantastic, and you can tell it was done with great care and attention to detail.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Patrick M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIiLW1EQ4A7kNKeqQ_xaXYEMzEl7z1ICVIUpqcjBk_BHiwfcQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Our house is a 2200 square foot two story with an almost flat roof.  Very slight pitch.   We received a competitive bid for a new membrane roof to replace the existing torch down roof and downspout system.   We also felt the most comfortable with Jack K. who came out and provided the bid.    We left during the installation which was amazingly quick and came back to a beautiful new roof and downspout system.    You'd never know anyone was even there as they did a great job with clean up.    Our crew was led by Jose and our office communication was with Matt W. who also responded every time within minutes to our many questions.    Jack also drove from south King County to north Seattle during rush hour to show us downspout color samples because we couldn't really determine a match with the online options.    That was great service and very much appreciated.  We highly recommend Three Tree Roofing.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Gabi Gebauer","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU4QjzklL60Avd2KXT2nIqSSs_EuLKo_J6uRjv3tentXSgA-89j=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Our realtor recommended Three Tree to us and we had bids from 2 other roofing companies but went with Three Tree due to their responsiveness, friendliness, and price - they weren’t the least expensive but their service was worth a little extra to us. Their crew was prompt, got the job done quickly, and left everything cleaned up. I’d recommend Three Tree to anyone looking for a new roof!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Domino Birze","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUdV66gDkm8Hl8UilfL3etd1QTYm2EV-ultsL7ZmvUHnuJR69V7=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Three Tree roofing did an amazing job on our roofing project. They're very responsive, and everyone I communicated with on the team was very friendly and respectful. There was a delay completing our project because of our skylight, which we had them replace, was a very custom size and they had to reorder a new window with the correct dimensions. While waiting for the window to come in they maintained ongoing communication to keep my looped in on timeline. I would highly recommend Three Tree to anyone with a roofing project - they're really are the absolute best!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Randy Hernandez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXXkAbBGbZQTm1PkuZcr5XXQsPr2worB_ajhgyi7RDQd1r7hPo7=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We loved our experience with 3-Tree Roofing, starting with our Sales Consultant Caleb, our PM Jake and our Foreman Johnny.  The communication and response time was great, the professionalism by all was impressive.  Plus the quality products and long warranty coverage was a big reason I selected this company.  I appreciated how well they cleaned the yard and picked up any leftover nails.\nWe were not planning on getting a new roof, but when we were getting bids for going solar, we found out our roof needed replacement first.  3-Tree worked directly with the Solar company to ensure the proper 'ice shield' was applied on the sections getting solar to ensure those sections stayed water tight during the installation process of the panels.\nHere is an after pic (should have taken a before).\nMore than satisfied with the entire project!\nLiz and Randy H","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0m5HY0EbXtsFDQCK6iYLo_rXz-_L-RRJKxYFovYc6JBeAOFgzGIo_kMG6qsKqb-YEsDuXbJwHPsDmcRpLe81psia0xNNChFNojYFJKsisgv-yN7zfRrydnwumJG-7alqZFahZRaw=k-no"],"When":"2024-11-27"}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
