.googleusercontent.com/gps-cs-s/APNQkAETLtIFxe_A7kigfq9V0M_w6ahLZir-cdX6j8aFE0FmQRJ8C9xYxF7OAuQHUcL9cJTD9H4uVqeIgjd00JPIRI2kxXM0H8gqUluEqWZpBwiV150oUZq7M2wUNwfr-LTVj2fX6k8KCuBmV8yf=w312-h298-k-no"},{"title":"House","image":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/gps-cs-s/APNQkAET3sUZEBBWyNbMwi5bUYrB0hJy8YlCN5wFVBxlSnT_l-5ixYzcSWoqxiON7tVh5YqOEE-cAvGlIwidtoiN69HREJHlNk6NsQh0Vbhh6waIMK44xUVG1PN0qmI-kxj2IS9J5fGMbg=w397-h298-k-no"},{"title":"Roof shingle","image":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/gps-cs-s/APNQkAFl2flvbO6XvBBIWsk6WG8u0H2kCcsBpxCbphtqqSmJybTuLa56xIMKHAh_euTfL7dKRLDn4D4zeDm8UEXuMoVFrWthy3WgjcyzhrWvD-UPFoAYU33vFfWXyYmSNx9NQanQb24m8A=w397-h298-k-no"},{"title":"By owner","image":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/gps-cs-s/APNQkAFWtxza4sGjmG57gYY8n-4YV1t9B8PkSMHhmItrJVhyhB9UbAH7eVufnuJ3UBueiGwswPTVvQWDK4O6crcYii-l7gSGmG_xDdsJT6hUx0_IoaS-DTfkyoLj3OtJj2HPPVuc-yvtLQ=w397-h298-k-no"},{"title":"Street View \u0026 360°","image":"https://streetviewpixels-pa.googleapis.com/v1/thumbnail?panoid=PRoumTLaKQmZJ9Pk7D2RVA\u0026cb_client=maps_sv.tactile.gps\u0026w=224\u0026h=298\u0026yaw=125.823006\u0026pitch=0\u0026thumbfov=100"}],"reservations":null,"order_online":[{"link":"https://larryhaightroofing.com/free-estimate/?utm_source=gbp\u0026utm_medium=organic\u0026utm_campaign=local","source":"larryhaightroofing.com"}],"menu":{"link":"","source":""},"owner":{"id":"104764657587453343787","name":"Larry Haight's Residential Roofing Company, Inc. (Owner)","link":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104764657587453343787"},"complete_address":{"borough":"Sammamish Valley","street":"15203 NE 95th St","city":"Redmond","postal_code":"98052","state":"Washington","country":"US"},"about":[{"id":"service_options","name":"Service options","options":[{"name":"Online estimates","enabled":true},{"name":"Onsite services","enabled":true}]},{"id":"accessibility","name":"Accessibility","options":[{"name":"Wheelchair accessible entrance","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible parking lot","enabled":true}]},{"id":"parking","name":"Parking","options":[{"name":"Free parking garage","enabled":true},{"name":"Free parking lot","enabled":true},{"name":"Free street parking","enabled":true},{"name":"On-site parking","enabled":true}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Yuan Li","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUj9ynOOfPpmiDahXgBkwdVDlUgz-j5MJ41yWOxYMpZhuZ9ZLsm=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had several referrals to use this service, and I expect great service and outcome. The experience was excellent until I saw the final delivered product. In the material/fix list it was stated using white board that match the damage roof, and here is what it I get, a yellow non matching one.\n\nHope I can get it fixed and will update the review accordingly.\n\n12/11 updates: Appreciate the owner clarifying that “white wood” is a building material type, not a color. Since we have white trim, that term—combined with the estimator giving my wife a “perfect fix”expectation —led us to expect a visual match, not yellow primer. I suggest the company clarify that painting is still required, as the jargon is particularly misleading when repairing white trim. I’ll work with Larry Haight’s to have this fully painted and resolved. Will update the review further after follow-ups.\n\n12/12 updates：The follow-up was promptly scheduled, and the crew onsite was very professional—arrived on time and did a fantastic job. Given the earlier hiccup, I appreciate the extra effort Larry Haight’s put in to meet customer expectations even more. It really shows they care. What a great company. Highly recommend! 5 stars, since I cannot add more.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3LF8Gj9DTBfUs4JFVPrbkUr_YIw20BPusNVT0WUc_8WvxJejIJEoyGghKEq7u_RJyW3EcGZm1MmpmNYWyvkRh_TZv3ub6kSXQRfrptfizVIUWZxOZOXB8l_I6H6Sfq2B4VQDcKRSWXutI=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2VCx4ZCmQ0WvK6JLKrtEEIuvUNX7pzxsUTBtrNUPPMlY2lrW0cZzlA8aX3L7DuLfEvFVK21cXC8o0S7-ikpNAz0UFeNGeK-uQdGgy4f9tgrr-N--7uGt00iwao6S4qRFOAz46pZFM67k0=k-no"],"When":"2025-12-10"},{"Name":"Amy Hong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX9eGAubjpBcbofZoiCCqTRKnlhVX34aIHMlB6bRCTeeJEYaEk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"They did my roof a few years ago and it still looks beautiful. The crew was friendly, courteous, and helpful as they helped us out with a few requests too. They were not the cheapest bid but I'm glad we went with them because their work turned out as excellent as they promised and it's comforting to know the most expensive upgrade in the house was done well.\n\nSome things to note. We had a siding guy come fix our chimney siding and he damaged some new singles. Larry Haight sent out someone to fix the damages for a very reasonable cost. Much appreciated!\n\nThey replaced vent ducts so they go out the roof instead of poorly out the soffits.\n\nDuring the final walk through, I pointed out a few drip edges that didn't quite reach the edge of some fascia. They were happy to fix them. Otherwise there have not been any issues worth calling out.\n\nIt's been a few years and I still catch myself stopping to admire the roof. Sounds kinda silly after typing that out 😅 but I do!\n\nWe are so happy with their work we referred them to family who is now scheduled for a new roof.\n\nI'll update this at needed.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Clemmie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLxp3sw4LdMQvq-DpCZkOcL22aEeNUcWR_MWAwliiDV1OR5NA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had our roof installed and had a crew of nice workers for a few days. They did a great job and they were very professional. They cleaned up the surrounding areas,  made sure there wasn't any nail on the ground. When they left the site, it was always nice and clean.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Chris Main","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWemn-m9l5um04RFL6bONpZcEtj5aGkFAKnvy9mQ8ne_KXfBLZ28g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Overall one of the best experiences I have had with what is one of the most daunting home improvement projects one can take on. From sales, office staff, work crew, and ownership, the staff across the board is A+.\n\nWe used Larry Haight’s Residential Roofing to replace our end of life torch down roof with a new IB PVC roof. We had received bids from multiple contractors for our job, varying from replacing with TPO or PVC, and the bid from Larry Haight’s was competitive, but we thought that the IB PVC product was just the best material for our 1927 home to last for years to come. Outside of the competitive bid and product, what set Larry Haight’s apart from the others was their old fashioned and professional approach. Mike came out and was very knowledgeable off the bat about what needed to be done on the initial roof inspection. Other companies from this point would just email me their bid, but Larry Haight’s sent George out to explain the bid to us in detail and to answer any questions for us. This was no-pressure, old fashioned, and very much appreciated. When we decided to choose Larry Haight’s, George came out again to go over everything once more.\n\nUpon signing, we then worked with Heidi \u0026 Shirley, who were both always there to answer any of our questions and keep us updated around scheduling. From signing to completion took about 5 1/2 months, but that is to be expected during the rainy season and with a flat roof. During this time, we had a minor leak due to some flashing around a chimney, and Larry Haight’s sent someone out the next day to wrap our chimney until they could come out to do our job.\n\nWhen our job started, the crew showed up on schedule and were ready to go. The crew was also very knowledgeable, professional, and approachable whenever I had questions. They were also very meticulous and would tell me they needed to replace something that I would have never been the wiser. The crew took great care of the property while they were here, and I also noticed that their trucks were also in tip-top shape as well. I never had a doubt that we were in good hands. It ended up raining on the day our project started, and the crew secured everything and came out during the storm the next day to ensure our roof and home were safe. Taking off a roof and having it rain sounds very stressful, but I felt like we were in good hands with this group.\n\nFinally, once the job was complete, Mike came out to do a final inspection, and Michael Haight met with us as well to discuss how our project went. Aside from this roof, we had a small section of tile roofing that also needed attention. Larry Haight’s recommended a contractor who could do this roof for us, and we went with them as well and had the same experience as we had with Larry Haight’s. Others would just say “we don’t do tile roofs” or would opt to replace it with asphalt shingles on a 1927 Spanish Style stucco bungalow…no thanks. All in all, I couldn’t have asked for a better experience during one of the more daunting home improvement projects, and we definitely made the right choice.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2qKMoeZjDg26yxK8KBeGm-Dj59uWvUQ0nWNT6T1ucWgxWMCsLmkBvNBrN6KImDS_na1wKv0Letak29L-aNRNTblCDx_UUMlp3ukt-5_qavGH-AC3JsLGauDPfLgzuOz6ZUjtVOZg=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0Au5IFQNEcII6lt9K20GXIrepdO1TY3DKtN0ALj3FpMlOgf008KMkQ0erPqxeshN-zXe-6_ejIvMkXv_dffjm3TTRDG68WsRyNonxB7kqfIWAAxFyfP8h_WaubiDC9OSOy3ajx=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0d0J6m4crR5EDdYc_0_FEfFZV7U-L0UHZZ0NWh8EtCFuEnQzDwJloDWFg2_VvcHrRfs0o6ugusrJaFPOll2siJgueGDsQzH1sU8R4Vl5_ujhbGxMX7e31RIf5ZF15RQfXCWQnjMw=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1WWcYofmNvOWJVlFvVwuDQ-4lxThhewQNfKNH3K3EFp5SaRkjo3S3-S63l_23nfsULvZptz9r0TI7wSTAPjc4z29hC--Q6fBwVmEUBfs_NsLWhNxULVa-x2nY1efh0ugR5Z0m_=k-no"],"When":"2023-3-9"},{"Name":"Taegan Fogg","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLSBgvoJYMHTYmTIAMywF4SXXouRLbOCTL3CbCfC0gOS1gawA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I hired Larry Haight's Residential Roofing to replace my torch down tongue and groove flat roof with IB.  After the Bomb Cyclone November storm, I hired them again to repair my IB flat roof.  I worked with Randy \u0026 Heidi May on these projects as well as a different estimator and project manager for the repair.  They did a quality job.  I would hire Larry Haight Roofing again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"John DeVitis","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWuZdNnlJu8QqeTpQowEeaHchwT86Q3qPUOrRt_iX_G2zn_IuQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Having the roof replaced on you home is one of the scariest \"remodels\" imaginable. It's disruptive, potentially damaging, and of course costly. So you want to make the right decision. We had estimates from 4 roofers..we chose Haight because they were easy to work with, priced right, and included all the important elements we learned about from gathering estimates.  Ultimately they did exactly what they said they would and then some. A polite crew, careful with the landscape and responsive to questions. A project manager who was here every day and followed through on little things without any extra effort on our part. The result is better than I imagined. I highly recommend Haight.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1geO15xD1z-L84M2KzEYadfI0bXEX5yc6PWet5SDnugK8hVET-oNuJ57Dp_g6s6XwjQV4hC4EnvWuPosnr11gqP0Hx7bOxmSI-Y_aIIy6FvP96KsZmwmDbA0ynI9RKman0nld-YPoqAwc=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2ohXAzDb1cwuXNr3DaPF7rSt_8gqHR9NiCvagpV0WUIfvL-4Wp5NnLY6nc81TEkbkZntd7NdZ0lUtUOJYMon2eu4XKsn0urXf3NvXmdlR0SUretcp4GNVYPqHmN2tEN3KT76S_pZ-R5n0=k-no"],"When":"2025-7-8"},{"Name":"Flying Fish","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWg2mj-ax_cI6di0zU5wv67T3KegM9jMS_IEkRE3waQ1XE_9Aig=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Was very impressed with all the staff and workers, and with the quality of their work. Very professional and detail oriented. They were on time and on budget. They care about customer satisfaction. I was actually a bit shocked when I got the initial bid for a full roof replacement, it was a lot lower than I was expecting.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Rudy Lim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWkXQuC1UCBbHQHNUpreDtocnoO6Beuy-tAHtgD03c1UbI1h-U=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Absolute 6-star experience with Larry Haight's crew. Very thorough and professional from the beginning of sales through the last step of payment. Amazing roof like everyone else have said!!","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
