enabled":true},{"name":"Onsite services","enabled":true},{"name":"Language assistance","enabled":false}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Roger Parker","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX-GySDuS9AchFgbsOb4TDaYMBsR8cwKMFKcFJfSpHgwuK33wT4Dw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A work of art! So impressed with the design and workmanship that went into the creation of our roof. Equally impressed by the quality of the installers who were focused and professional and delivered the job on time. The central  office managed the schedule perfectly, kept us informed throughout and were always available and responsive.We always felt our job was the most important one they had. Good job Mountaintop Metal. You have a great team and product. We picked the right company!","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3BIG8Ol5h82qs1QkBhHAMhlEHcocZ-WCzuSDlcWCk36xWiVmH0IZpUnLkEuY_sHE7ISxZDO8Ygjx6imI1-2IHFUflMX3svrIjDBJMbRVb_8mJtB5UQilthxfnBAGiUGtw_8tJnH30VnJ4=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2A2AlTubIKNWE6Ph77j0FAyZJSbZRkdnY32AM0RCpvvlrg66h_3fDQYxa9UM1eqrMh641JLa9ORjWlhHqKEEvEhYrOCXYtzuIqi8d-47YqM92M_2qJRWXMnLf5FBirXkUMbT8OOgECwPGs=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2zRSkdG1SOcg9Os-X-PEsHsXtpPLVrwQu-7Te5dqlYMFhYZmYGeIzsgNPIjo59P4s8cXWI7viggJYiU2HHspYmC88q9caAKi5VYz1uuul9Bq9RyUKrcxFhd80RQmgOAA0uI5bBqE5x5lI=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0gnjxV__oKKfODxxUZS-vbRlEpdfJKi0BfKo8jcqlx5PJPqRiXP45OebITbaxUPARfWAPFQdd5v9ouZFb1rrXQmvVZ0N2Xu7YZXuMlIFpAE0c5ByW42QjTP5wskrK_i7iQ3dvbKXfgGWyz=k-no"],"When":"2025-7-28"},{"Name":"Eric Fortney","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW1pGWiCbTBIOOpKH2nCXsqheDphQ5AZhc8iOzMk8e-P1M6Rygz=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had a great experience with this company for replacing our old rotting asphalt shingle roof with a new green aluminum shingle one. The team was fast and professional with a clean installation.\n\nThey were very flexible with some last minute modifications such as needing to replace additional rotting fascia board and demolishing a back porch roof section to even out the roofline and open space for a future awning to which they worked around without any complication. Would recommend. Price was comparable to many asphalt shingle quotes for a much more durable product.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3hSzC-SduP-N4iou-neHeFm7NvWczx9F26et1BgssjhvipDeGvhfJgKwBXpRr5CEl-AftErNVdw04NH4v91LZk32KWxmur9Zp5h1S9LU2efIjK7xHrZ5TnbTCiih5P6XgQqI5E1fIlq6-0=k-no"],"When":"2025-11-19"},{"Name":"Michael Monroe","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL7Jjzk8bylORVoOCHJrmI0IbTEmbHBzA0dQKw9OQbzg3UaQg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We are very happy with our new roof. Mountaintop Metal roofing finished on schedule and we paid a fair price. Their professional crew kept the site clean and informed us of what they were doing. I highly recommend Mountop Metal Roofing","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"EC EC","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKQqOLjuvbe5us4Y5otdHYHuU9EcvKMrZhmRlVMDVHGFugMOg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Fantastic company to work with for your metal roofing needs.  Max provided a bid for my $65,000 job.  Although his bid was the most expensive, he was also the most thorough spending about 1.5 hours crawling in our attic and explaining the technical stuff about why their install team is the best.  The work crew were very responsive and I appreciated their thoroughness cleaning up after themselves.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Brittany Akkurt","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVMsZVb6pWXIUAbym-5Z5kWF0n6N8G7RVf2cJ0VrpMbV2nRhmQe-A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We met with 6 different roofing companies before landing on Mountaintop. Pricing-wise, Mountaintop was in the upper middle of the quotes - but we still felt very confident with the decision to select them. What made us select them was their personal attention, communication of our needs, product quality, warranties on the work and product, and the process they use to build the roof.\n\nAn extra shout out to Kailey with the office who was INCREDIBLY helpful throughout. When we ran into snags with the city and needed to schedule an electrical outage, she worked directly with the electrical company to confirm the needs and project timeline. When we wanted to ensure we had gutter providers lined up that worked with the new roof type, she connected us with a local company - and even worked with them directly to update timelines as the project dates shifted. When we wanted tinted skylights for our NINE custom skylights (which Mountaintop doesn't do), she found a trusted vendor and sent us tinting samples and cost comparisons of skylights so we had choices. Like literally, anything that we assumed we would have to deal with alone, we didn't because before we could even start, Kailey was already on it and had solved any problems that came up.\n\nOur original project manager/sales person transitioned out of the company before the project started, so the company owner, Glen took on our project. He gets an extra shout-out too. It was clear from the start that Glen knows his stuff and how to engage with clients who don't know anything about roofing - he was able to explain things clearly and provide the \"why\" for certain things that needed to be done. As we hit hiccups, Glen worked to find reasonable solutions - and went above and beyond to ensure that we were satisfied with the outcome. He really looks out for the customer - and wants to make sure that they are feeling confident throughout the process. Glen was very communicative, and we felt comfortable reaching out as much as we needed.\n\nThe on-site crew did great work on both the demo of the old torch-down roof and installation of the new metal roof. They demoed some outdoor pergolas that were going to impact the gutter placement, and made sure that we had pictures of the roof progress. We are happy with the installation crew and appreciate the very, very long days that they spent on the project. They finished on time, which was great considering we anticipated having to go over based on some surprises that were found once demo started.\n\nOverall, while I'm hopeful and confident we won't need a roof replacement in the next hopefully-bazillion-years, if we ever did, we'd be reaching back out to Glen and his team at Mountaintop Metal Roofing. 10/10","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3h-NlhUsrlhowNzooeUDKYcSvwO32Gzylg2WQ5i7IwrAcGyASXW7-0Oi85wMABbwZKyk2DZ77P2VXooKFkuJbbWwDYKH9RXwXtRwO4x1olz6u5bREwAL6RAa_rkE7Z4I0TgVihbw=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1NgLLdNzqjrg7gWIsorSL5BZnkAX60jLaNM4HTd2R3IdvSsouWReC1lsFhymKv873m7mkCaHxT1xcFR2HeQ8Ck561YaRokaRGKl1UYmmXlpsGP0fQt7SLKAgZGKnwTAow5d5HS=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn396DaHyk7QYecT64wncHJgyyoWwfwdcPTpuJMKk9mMvfgHw_x9xCZOBMZhbSqyVSlBBqVap7nIwIeZ7J80u7r6gKAmvCIL5iTBxOlbCjNkJcWkAohAaPziQt078ARDnVxni9f1dQ=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3GCQNtkJbVOms_7pSvEV0c6SQUUs64LhVf-X9XNJLCavNN2I5wPOj7o9-AiKEAePSR5smfPLBNd3wmIc-yzP-k7REWsHF8oHtxoLqTPocljuC7QUP-__OrPPxCA7kIpj-O97c=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3a6hu83HvThBkC-2k3e_h06cdfEbnMoDMn-a0Mn5woTZTB8x6Lwieu9f8c34dpS2UygISWDh0sGXp6kqg6737Pmpln48xhtuA2rcl0dUItGS1kbLyp1pMgQGCBmcZNSGwTAdqu=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1bJxfmAJDCXs1DIabDdpfRbBJBlTzmwqVHNELM0xguxJpD-xmRuO4O7ddmEq2rgKV8jzPr8M3suhh5DpjEAnSXSohKkW2DnPjueA5-khB4AiizhxONWYpK05Y1vuDls1Bf4WWe=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3Y4rA9oDWKEDcvN2pirWX7ECgRhIS97FpjyYstVhVe_9c12kM5s_ZfrSMJ0Yt5p5PMmJMHcZ1ZNSPKOnuOiMgwMhbriSN0AsUmQwu82mjNCfayyqsWulQGDpVM3Fhi2tv5QoJfSg=k-no"],"When":"2024-8-6"},{"Name":"Celine \u0026 Nick FUiller","