rge crew, and, even from long distance, they had great communication. Very trust worthy! I recommend!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Dean Davison","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIn7jTZTWa_XFDI9HOx1nOVhjAoi0bhho12VdEMRVFVwzQ3xg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Professional, Transparent, Experienced, and Focused on Quality\n\nAfter 48 years of homeownership, this was my first full roof removal and replacement. I interviewed five companies (all chosen for their reviews and experience) and Tekline stood out from start to finish.\n\nFrom the first call to scheduling, the estimating process (thank you Jose), and the entire installation, Tekline was consistently professional, organized, and transparent. They never over-promised and always delivered.\n\nThe installation team, led by Ernesto with oversight from Tha Khun, worked efficiently, respectfully, and with great care for our property. Robert, the Production Manager, followed up personally to ensure every detail met our satisfaction. Elia was a pleasure to work with on the billing side—friendly, responsive, and professional.\n\nEven after the project was signed off, Tekline returned immediately to address a couple of small items—no hesitation, no hassle. Their focus on customer satisfaction is clear at every level of the company.\n\nI can say with confidence: you can trust Tekline Roofing in every aspect of your roofing project.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3eTrXbzeE2KODC_pagQSmPK38UnK9VpzYkmOHA_1lkI2DCkzs9wIEMqXPCKsa_TBfHuhBxxamHPs18vckGQUTJtlaykfeckqeNiOi2mPSa5uTc6COqss9JLRReQKh_M_EMZFyZQ85u3-5_=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn15nxxg5rVxviNt7n0p_Fw9B2FtMOeobQE2vog9Zx97F79J2oQGCu5nlY6NquZOikghf192ohk6omyqXhw3FShdZovhVTJswYk17sgeQtCxz_KfM0nZGBh7vdMWEuwaW9EDE4aeMUvTOG2y=k-no"],"When":"2025-8-22"},{"Name":"Van Jensen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXDjeqbamF_Gi3Oq9wTYJgui3tSilVI3oHAJ0mG3BNNRbWqTQGB=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I found Tekline based on couple of recommendations from neighbors. Tekline replaced a torch down roof with a PVC membrane roof on my house. I was impressed with the level of professionalism and the quality of the work. The whole job took two and half days. Everything turned out great and working with Tekline was very easy.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0vycdURUP4PYhA4IvJRsjL3dLjKxJUppSoA4qP3zirx1hQF-xziMF2zn7byvCiW7ne3iMaU_nBYxydZSX_44X6yCTBvH_F27N1VgW0px5voFgp_JHEILRErSNxedgIDsvTSm2y=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2wYcs3OXXKyclydvuXJpTQZ7oVH8G-9EabGfSvX5HCAwdi_N3pNObtq1FCEJZ11EsPVGJBYcQzo96IbGsZG1CUCsCDQB1tVdChLA59mcHKyrowCh_Kr_Xdp--SKI_CUTb7JZ0E=k-no"],"When":"2025-4-18"},{"Name":"Evelyn Liebscher","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI-ilc7zcnMQsbwaz8Fmrx9lRY4Xf92qUGlvOd2tPj2gxAZTA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had our roof replaced by Tekline in April 2025 on a very old rental property. The replacement was required by our homeowner’s insurance company, which made timing and budget especially important. After researching and getting quotes from four well-reviewed companies, I chose Tekline because of their strong warranty, longevity in the business, and consistently positive customer feedback.\n\nFrom my first interaction, I was impressed. Tekline responded to my quote request within minutes and scheduled an onsite visit within the week. Their estimate included detailed photos, measurements, and even an attic inspection — which none of the other companies offered. Jose Bejarano, the estimator, walked me through every line of the quote and was patient and thorough. While their price wasn’t the lowest, it was fair. When I explained my budget concerns, Jose spoke with the owner, Scott, and they worked together to help me meet my budget without sacrificing quality materials.\n\nThey understood the urgency of my insurance deadline and scheduled the job accordingly. Since I live out of the area and couldn’t be on-site, I asked if they could send progress photos — and Tekline was the only company that not only agreed, but said they do this routinely for all clients. That gave me peace of mind that they’d use the specified materials and follow every step of the process properly.\n\nBefore the project started, they emailed a helpful prep guide I could forward to my tenants. During the project, I received daily email updates with photos and a summary of the work completed. The job was done in just a couple of days, came in exactly as quoted, and the finished roof looks great. See photos. We went with CertainTeed shingles in Black Walnut color","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3Rj2aiYR0Xp4tCFO4TA8zTGMbzxuO1RlqO0yhtnmoLPuyA8asQI0Un-exFZq47QoCQUTCSa4Hhf8BdDkkCZgt2f7VWZtUlctzMQpDaSJNNcPKzm5_frxncMVBA5b_uTVTJJuhXbw=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3UGEBCiFU_omiJcvTZzXlnts9HIGv5tbJz_0OOXUOQnCJ-GF7GlTvA2hGTqe5U7n6r_HrnvYiJUowHefxJa2DdiBw1SFNZGEeQTHUefupvQXXBG_ZXskeCtwWBUNbASiNOjCQ=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0JBWCqV5ICAU-zoRcfYZltwxbx-rpUn1bf72etL785JS1_wZqGrL55FHy3q92aIiw2I-dBxe8mmoE4-Wque0WkfYw1GB4B7Q9JMBMEOYxwSnywbZdHoLddS2A-QGAMRV24S5hGFw=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1gCyUfajmrmy75TjdTSz7-E6bc-jN77B9dWo6jwowc0adDUVh9nKIGlWjvO1vFtvelpSoyIR6DwdwyEhh5DSjI2cXnYo1HtjLqRj0O6eas7NROB6TGTml4tMAJQKd4GLarB177=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1NJcgrOsTFhBjKLFz3KD9arA9mvrClhSNy-tw7or7IJ5w-F69JZaMLGG_6xHsv8M3vrYEtLT8W0W6sj5gzyBdJw0XMLws32p7vYKEXm9UvrlUQXQE7qe20kEd-pR0yUje6hmeRUA=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1iiPS1F__U_ToGEZ6bnP1H-A5Pa3uEVUprCMlI_Dkw8ClAts2cELy46U-fAHT81Nib2zi0bbcBRKQc042-CYsgmvR2v9jIUE25GkEvBu_DioLgVNQkv4tOygw2FkvLZ4q_U6VX=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn19h4yMerTCZ-m3jPXzWqqd2gykp1ptC0oQzsfGE6gks-IV9na-R4jSHyBC-tcdThPhJmAkafN5NEKFCvhRCPfTzVJLGf05Mr96FSOpA5oG705lwv3W93gv6LO9Ew-KYJpIFFH9=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0ieV75RtpBunN8YH-e17ZpztgT3hg27B3Ycy-uPvoc4RfOliA-FkY0-YlpWuAJmYKcodpdspuqFvEf8xYCNPayMkqMlGk3Ys5U4P7edtmbHgNnOs5QEe9A-ss90w_uWTu0dT5Hng=k-no"],"When":"2025-6-2"},{"Name":"Anthony Elarth","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUHZuA5oWXKZ4PV4DHy0uBavChSELNRZweabck_o31l2P28E5jW=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had a WONDERFUL experience with Tekline and HIGHLY RECOMMEND them for your new roof.\n\nJust a few aspects of the experience that I appreciated so much.\n\n1) DAILY STATUS EMAILS.  The project lead sent me an email every evening at work stop to explain progress during the day, photos of that progress and plans for the next day (arrival time, work focus).  I wasn't expecting this - it felt very \"white glove\" and I wish all contractors did something similar.  It helped me feel like the project was under control and since the photos were usually from the rooftop, they showed angles that I'd never see myself.\n\n2) POST-COMPLETION ATTENTION.  After the project was essentially complete, I flagged two concerns.  Tekline - without hesitation - heard me out and put time and attention toward the fixes.  One was completely aesthetic and was fixed right away.  The other turned out to be totally unrelated to the roof project at all - but Tekline still sent people twice to my house to inspect and uncover the root cause.\n\n3) UTTERLY PROFESSIONAL / FRIENDLY.  Across the entire project, I interacted with probably ten people from Tekline.  From reception to sales/contracting to project management to the daily crew, every person was professional, respectful and friendly.  And every time they said they'd arrive for an appointment (initial estimate, drop off shingle samples, post-completion inspections), they were right on time -- same goes for the daily start times with the roofing crew.\n\n4) HONEST.  Separate from the new roof project, Tekline noted a couple areas where my roof awnings were sagging.  Certainly seemed like the kind of thing to address while putting on a new roof - but I was curious about how much of an issue/risk it truly presented, beyond aesthetic.  I asked the Tekline carpenter lead that very question and was surprised when his reply was essentially: \"well, they've probably been sagging like this for decades - they've probably stabilized and won't get much worse in the future.\"  He could have told me the roof was going to fall in and I would've believed him!  I ended up agreeing to do the work, despite the low urgency/risk and criticality.\n\nI could go on, but those items truly stand out.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0Aw2zp2Yms_fSPRlmAKk37NfBrJI7wekhRDzOfXnMkEwqtQeCBEWdoprb1x64iKBHTgEleC26cmTXNASnYlU_JPRxN8TwO_DOvVMXGFdQr8Bpv1zVhXOuzbF6A559B4uUC8iuz=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0HE_KPImER7XhaWMITmsGgPmYD9DYZY1Ebrt_eJ_kr2TeMJ2nI_sju9v46VfmS4QBvWkTGRzRb0-fmmUIcGspa5cQQuhO_r_lyrm5_W1hDye3da4wFWoEEomFh2W4fwpqmAUWhJA=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0ruptqmR0_R6Wc53seChoKKTKbQjKe-4Aijl_hYudGL_5SjiWPMTsiej-51dVTWuzqmtW6Dp-sBoBrz2EnWghwCbaZnuwPKBNWFkceaU0Qga9qS6V3L0MVCsylrPVp0_7cBcw=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2bkNa5Iv1YxIgqEEpdtLL5Utl3ANflT7fnAxPZwg6c9unxS0OaeuNQxgOxj1VKY8Wy-YRS7e0mr5Jn_sconD_JjyX_OtR4GRDP-GKQGjIwuo2wQS-3wpKC8ePaKfc-nCC3jR6sYg=k-no"],"When":"2025-2-20"},{"Name":"DW Bowers","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKOf9qcUdcvYX0gJZTcAOYsMh-GU_akgZbsE3fI1xKd4ogNXA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We were unfortunate to have a tree fall on our house in December from the \"bomb-cyclone\" storm.  Fortunately we got a quote from Tekline and several other roofing companies and we chose Tekline to replace our roof.  Norm was great to work with and he worked with our insurance company to get them and us the info we needed for our insurance claim reimbursement.  Our next door neighbors were so impressed with our roof they asked me for the name of the company and their relative had Tekline replace their roof too.  We are very pleased with our roof.  It looks better than before and has better ventilation too.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0oIWVn1k6Nyk8keRHxbnMAa7xN4GtdQBnaATTmdnY0nab4xIfg49FC1M9-FbPwCgyIhkiv6ldQAgSxfnBiz1nyAiF4Gp0HXLdiRtvQjUOCY5-Ye0sF-XOUDku6b_1l70ePkIb3=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3z8qPUJ3Sm4T6B78axGhmej2InveH0oqLbow7lSyzLliL_xqOzNfAyXUCYx204Y_rDFi_cUDiyhFbJ9Jq1KxWczKl_IrKDCMqknqxoyJ0Hr-FnSOCXx8LQRmcJdWdi7TfUsN356A=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2UBJd81kOcPhe46EhSNXB-r-qSjPzVo_qT3LTrb6UOL6-skiKr3kR7Wf1886BVQra9_fcfxjrLlmIGUfEcIkpXBJMZmjfImnntz9wH6q8rnj7b3q1avbtKoDBePdjN3b_l9w2y=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn05tchhzh-yfu6FG3jTudtUESME36V9sfOVEzbWmwqB7hFKhAlTDDTaTDNLKM9u6Nmz2Ns3ooiEKCZDTk90gG6MCOgVO7SvQ2uAqm7pWkTG4J5QsWJeWc9E9whKGxvQDH43Xl-v9w=k-no"],"When":"2025-1-15"},{"Name":"Tammy Mcguinness","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVtKiEraBRJvhsa-flv-XnQ2LPTVIpcc_Wh_fqfN4TypNJor14=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I cannot recommend Tekline Roofing highly enough. I originally contacted them to reseal some plumbing pipes on our top floor, and they were out the very next day. However, the next night, I discovered a major leak in a completely unrelated section and level of the roof. I walked into our main floor restroom at 10:30 PM to find water flowing through the light fixture.\n\nI messaged them late that night, and despite it being a different area than their initial work, they had Manual, one of their flat roofing crew leaders on-site by 1:00 PM the next day. He quickly identified that this specific section had been poorly installed by the original builder.\n\nWhat impressed me most was their proactivity. Because our house has three levels with various roof sections, I asked them to check the rest of the home. They identified similar installation flaws on the other levels that would have eventually failed, and they are now fixing those as well. With all the kids coming home for Christmas, the peace of mind they provided is priceless. They are responsive, professional, and truly look out for the homeowner. Highly recommended!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Angie Romischer","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJglqin7rvV2G10iWiQ0xZPO_YXs6RkDRS_8XGIL_vpVy-y9Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I highly recommend Tekline Roofing!  We had a situation where we detected a leak coming into our home after seeing some paint bubble up on our interior wall.  When our roof blowers were here doing maintenance, she thought the roof felt soft, which was odd given the roof is only 10 years old.  Thinking we were looking at a roof replacement so soon, we decided to call roofers for their assessment.  The first company that came out, which gets rave reviews, said the roof installation done 10 years ago from the previous owners was \"shoddy\" and that the ventilation wasn't adequate.  He proceeded to quote us $55,000 to replace our roof.\n\nFollowing this, Norm from Tekline came out and took a very different position after making his assessment.  It happened to be raining when he was here and after checking the location of the bubbled paint, he found the source of the leak, one of which had nothing to do with the roof, rather, when we had work done to our balcony some years ago, they didn't use a waterproof caulk.  Norm found another small location on our roof that needed caulking due to I think some nails that had gone awry if I recall correctly.  Also rain had been dripping just inside or below the gutter.  I thought it was a gutter issue.\n\nNorm caulked both areas and the leak around the gutter stopped immediately and hasn't returned (and he didn't charge us).  It's been about a month.  As for the soft spot on the roof, he said this was normal wear and to have him come out again this summer when everything is dry to take another assessment.\n\nWhen we do need a roof replacement, we'll be calling Tekline.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
