hS=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn01G0WHfOZ4sppHaxZrT1yexoM6pBYMiQlZGHyOen41j4YktCzx9MbitQjBw9OQ_JWfHur6n7i2UNcnQH21Z0NJ7x2ih0VjC3YslN2z3lj3hY5abjYjasKz7V89tPwrra6iQe2p6Q=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2YhOVu_D70-IZsQW38g_wy3WbxRtK23Drl3DSHhBK5cd1euW6XtgXbGtkO9zI5ZGRG-jVuB5FwNFUoQgUqRohafvxMfYW2Rbuv7gvy-NkSb9YXe_eXw5v5mMiAUsMvTmfze9pl=k-no"],"When":"2025-3-12"},{"Name":"Brittany Akkurt","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVMsZVb6pWXIUAbym-5Z5kWF0n6N8G7RVf2cJ0VrpMbV2nRhmQe-A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Working with Vasyl was incredible! From the start, when he and his colleague came over to talk through options, they demonstrated a lot of knowledge and experience - and answered all of our questions. I appreciated that they provided options and listened to what we were needing. They were also understanding of our cost concerns and long term plans for our roof replacement. We knew the skylights were in rough shape when we moved in, and of course the night we moved in they started leaking. We called up Vasyl and he worked to find an intermediate solution without needing to replace every skylight (which other vendors had said was required). He cleaned all of the gutter areas and scraped up all the old paint. I mentioned during the quote process that we would prefer to keep the sealant/paint white - which is not a standard color - and he found a way to make it white! When it rained somewhat unexpectedly after the sealing/painting (which disturbed the paint), Vasyl immediately came out the next sunny day and it now looks even better than it did the first time (which was already awesome). Overall, we are very happy with how the roof turned out.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2JD6ApVpEW4uGx5qLHn86-Th4mbWyBKGOPnjLDHpKyUqTXQupvaKa3vsYBVCs8xvO4mj-JyPGSd0UWdWD2oNH7ZfKATMcGVbMDM0j7dLD2h2qvwSG2ulEubTPV61SZ_MPuGotAKQ=k-no"],"When":"2023-4-28"},{"Name":"Karen Weiss","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVlpBfKmf1cb8IxW40zZ7YI1a77cM2Zpn3JEi7SpRzBaZN8n2c8pQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Ryan and Vasyl were fantastic to work with! The workers finished my whole roof in one day, it was 84° outside, during their afternoon break I supplied them popsicles that were greatly appreciated. They arrived early and left around 9pm. Chateau Green is my shingle color.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1CtfKbTgZUgq6ccXVpddO31cg-Q6PGoZoW-3G0r-jkIPRFvfv3DWQ38tFKRw5bFzdXN1m-BHAK7FU2H-QMtW2eAHm0GfsaUWmerbTkJdJYG9jUAZqOeHDfr0vAdcM9k8vgkzHihA=k-no"],"When":"2023-7-7"},{"Name":"czeskleba","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ9DUzAY3ChURLr0SWDMtoHAhrH6HVWHqnWb68Y2h-wjInzug=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"After experiencing an unexpected leak in our bedroom ceiling I made calls to several roofers seeking assistance.  Given the time of year (December) and the weather conditions I was not optimistic about getting a quick response. But Ryan called me back literally seconds after I'd hung up the phone, and he was able to come out and look at my roof the next day.  He gave me a detailed explanation of the issues and quoted competitive prices for both a smaller-scale fix or a complete replacement.  Based on the age of the roof and the issues involved we decided on complete replacement.  Because they were already working on another project near our home, Ryan was able to offer a significantly discounted price and a next-day start time for the job.  He was also willing to accommodate my work schedule by having the crew start later in the day.\n\nThe work crew was efficient and worked long hours (well past eight hours daily) and they were responsive to my concerns about mitigating runoff during construction.  When unexpected issues resulted in an expansion of the scope of work (replacement of 100% of roof decking) there was clear communication about the revision of price and timetable.  Throughout the entire process Ryan was always readily available, responding quickly to text messages at any time throughout the day.  The entire job was completed less than a week after my initial call.  I would recommend Archetype very highly... their quality of work is excellent, and their communication and customer service is truly exceptional.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Rita Alli","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIIe-OBoZiATtoFkeLa33OV6HGzfc4ArlOzn4Ovwcruyplz5w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We began hearing squirrels in the walls of our upstairs bathroom and suspected they may have gotten inside the roof.  After calling several roofing companies, who all said they don’t “inspect” roofs, I called Archetype Roofing.  Ryan answered the phone and after hearing my problem offered to come out the next morning.  Ryan and Vasyl both came, went on the roof, took photos and showed us the damage. It was time for a new roof.  We liked them very much and felt like their proposal was fair, so we agreed to have them do the work right away.  Throughout the 5 day process, they were communicative and highly responsive.  Their crew was top notch - thorough and professional. They went above and beyond in cleaning out the squirrel nest. From the very start, I felt like Ryan and Vasyl made our problem their problem and took great care of us. I highly recommend them.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Lida Wilson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKQs4v6LSQxZXQAMNH8jjEI5SsbxJN8L_7vMlMauFkjybFM7A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I really enjoyed working with Ryan and VASYL.  They were very thorough when expecting attic and roof. They took alot of pics and explained the damaged and listened to my issues on the subjects.  I appreciate the professionalism they and the whole team that worked on my roof.  They appreciated the portable restroom 🚻 I got for them.  Thank you all.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0XNu4NEJvhM7nntkb_hjulQ1CFk86gJClUhCZlmifsDdbAHFIbhTA4BWiSLsFTjOQwuuhSIuLCQV7R1hqeb7b2TcXObH9QBz01_Q60CRDJ061olWtDSteS-glWtRPTIi-VTrY1=k-no"],"When":"2023-6-27"},{"Name":"Robert Kimmerle","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJt86BygwOqPsnJNfIQszkCJ1seGtvZh93u7kqbRw7bIowA8g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Ryan and Vasyl were extremely through as we were having our roof inspected for solar panel installation. They were extremely honest and transparent with the inspection results and there were no surprises once the job started. Their roofing crew was on time, extremely professional, and cared how they left my property at the end of each day.\n\nI did have another company inspect my roof with in the same week, the price was almost the same, however, the other company missed 2/3’s of the problems found by Archetype Roofing Co.\n\nNever once did I feel like the communication was anything but GREAT, no matter the time or day, responses were timely, straight forward and truthful, which I appreciate. I felt as if,  I was their only job at the time. I am\n100% satisfied with Archetype Roofing.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Gerald Bodey","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK3K-vzQMA6PImxVTQKmoyfEnD10leUqVyusVTfwSFeubkMQg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I cannot say enough good things about Ryan Flegel and Archetype Roofing. I had set up with Evergreen Restoration to have some roof repair work done. They were nice but after a month of not getting a schedule date, a friend of mine recommended I reach out to Ryan. He took my call on the weekend and came out to do an estimate. Due to the urgency (It was holding up my solar installation), Ryan had a team out in a couple of days and they did an outstanding job.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
