":"On-site parking","enabled":true}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"PB","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLpdK0WLuErOzIDHqc7t1T5Pw8UaZHh5Yw4EISisltRRMb1Hw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We’re pleased to share our great experience with Asset Roofing Company in replacing our roof. We closed on our home in late September 2024, knowing it would need a new roof. Once settled, we requested bids from several companies in late November, including Asset Roofing. After receiving six bids from qualified companies, Asset Roofing stood out as the clear choice.\n\nOwner Anthony Langdon personally met with us at the house in late November to assess the scope of work. His proposal was thorough, competitively priced, and included an option to replace our gutters at the same time—an option we ultimately chose and are glad we did. The entire contracting process was smooth, efficient, and completed online.\n\nOur project manager, JR, kept us informed throughout the entire project, providing updates on material deliveries, the work schedule, and promptly responding to any questions we had—though there were few, thanks to the team's professionalism. The crew began work in late December and handled a few weather-related scheduling challenges with minimal impact on the overall timeline.\n\nThe on-site foreman and crew were outstanding—punctual, friendly, and courteous. They worked efficiently and made sure to clean up thoroughly at the end of each day.\n\nWe highly recommend Asset Roofing Company for their professionalism, competitive pricing, and high-quality work.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0dSo-vzCaPK4CAuYKxMYG79owBtxtrjd-ESvPXe0UnHhQjVxBA1OwmfN_ll4Krf0rCR08Ej_EOIM7VeYf1SYhG30F5kKPIJYDwxDL4xjds6JIxjU8Ul25BWeFmmGpzqKEeo--t=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2EnKOac3npqCWQnfZ5HUCz6HlwoAgzLnj50HT57tuhK8JiJ7031JUIfykcxzvIPxLQzTI8vCPgnMZnX_O0xLhT0PuOG1ksfuHxyBgH9FUbnLKO5ctJhSXliWclMLyea2FnPIl57A=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0Eli9IjunmS8Fm3uJSWLdAZ2lZw-o24_Gh3018UB-T8qBxSeWSDQpWCT20yi0o5s2FqyG2NnOi08RfOZ_IX6qYzRmhz3WsecnCwB-_HZ4--mUgBbKClFphaF76MgKraNIOOow=k-no"],"When":"2025-2-17"},{"Name":"Russ Olivier","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIfoSrLvflZ7iq6cnPknEaPGfDRz5F8eFItpYFfG9jFk_dHCQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I've paid them $50K for a deposit for a large commercial roofing project.  Despite numerous emails and phone calls I still don't have a firm project start date.  They were extremely responsive up front on the sales side, but as soon as it moved to someone managing the project and communicating the schedule and plans it's complete silence.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Matthew Ferguson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKWtDTJl2TG7vquiV9Pd8XfcPSkX1ih9CCAVSykhFm18xAAhQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Dishonest, lacking integrity.\n\nMy initial experience with Asset was good. I had a full roof install. The price was decent and they seemed nice.\n\nThe issue came later when I experienced problems with my dryer. Long story short, Asset installed a mesh screen on my roof vent, which is a violation of building code and caused lint backup which almost caused a fire.\n\nThankfully, I caught it in time. I reached out to Asset to explain the situation and asked if they’d cover the minimal costs to clean my dryer and vent.\n\nThis is where they shocked me. First, they said it wasn’t their fault because they didn’t know it was a dryer vent. After I said ignorance isn’t an excuse, they went to incredible lengths to dodge taking responsibility!\n\nNow, they’ve gone completely silent. I guess they got their money from me, so they don’t care anymore.\n\nI agree with Asset on this: your roof is a huge asset, so find a more trustworthy company with such an important part of your home.\n\nUpdate:\nI called your company dishonest. You then reply with several lies.\n\nYou said my roof was installed several years ago: it was installed March of 2024. Just over one year ago.\n\nYou said I have flex piping, which is not to code. Your tech that visited my house said I NEEDED flex piping. You have contradicted yourself. I replied to you and verified that I do not have flex piping. It is solid ducting. You have not responded.\n\nYou said you haven’t responded due to regional flooding. My communications with you are from the beginning of this month; well before the flooding.\n\nI’ve reached out twice for a resolution, yet you have not responded. Please take responsibility for your mistake and stop trying to turn this on me.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Shannon Kavanaugh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX-CtyFOgd8IaFaZyTsn4sCHecIrJeu3G9E8OytYjQU8Fn60T5_=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"After watching them put my neighbor's roof on, I was impressed by how clean they left the job site. I called them up and needed them to schedule me quickly so I could get the roof done before an already scheduled paint job. Art, Joyce, and Brenden, were able to accommodate. Jilten and his crew were super reliable, tidy, and did a quality job. Then Asset Roofing came back to ensure their quality met their own expectations. Awesome. I also truly appreciate their commitment to supporting veterans in the community.\n\nThanks Asset Roofing!","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn16t723ssOkmFo8DiagiGMpU-yr8oHrnYV-_aeaw8G_ZZHVsFgYHk2UTTugxfNptvXVjLEfSpDwAysU75QKwYi7TDpACvoFAQzs3q2IVZ0OOC1EAmj1WGBiwaLPIrpp2a2b7SYK=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3WrBudC9CAmq7TpS2eMzS7noQg1f8uFdeAkCLvOqMBguCghCdLEi4fnZ5ih4cbvUa7QFDVNqSZAYtpV7YgvKf6F18TA3v5-a6BkOENNBID8sZ9KTEE_puwHBckm6l36twyb6S-OA=k-no"],"When":"2024-5-9"},{"Name":"Coach Kohler","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLHheKT-gD-wXC8j-WuDFFa91AnY38_ppBP5WUYnU8s4BklPg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rati