 of the job, we had a  handful of things we wanted addressed and they were taken care of.    We thought the bids were fair and realistic. A few recommendations: To save money, if you don't know exactly what you want, pay a few thousand dollars and hire a design consultant for layout, lighting plan, electrical plan, etc. When you hire one of these design/build contractors they charge you $50k for 3k worth of work. Alfredo often knows what will look good and not and what works well and not but it's not his job to design your remodel.  He will do what you ask him.    Make sure you have all the materials you are responsible for on hand, ready to be installed.  We slowed them down a few times by not having door hardware, paint, grout, etc.  Lastly, clarify exactly what materials are covered in the bid and which are not. Alfredo is a great communicator and even better guy.  The contractor profession needs more people like him.  We know you will be happy with Vasa Construction!","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2cS5o2ho5bTmfwycItzJyZucdIRHtswVVgLERowL9hBt5to6b5kZNgMQPSZwRMFK3hJpYU70xvPq_TpZqMX1R7vMU4QIBy7dsGRqbfEOyH-zKHO-aywxyMBfdu2ZW9DDCi7Q6q0Q=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1GL0Yl1Uwv15ToVSjJxKSGcIt9OPTKL_7__zhb6GnSCk7_w8czvB_MN8SJSuOZHyHURhSVve1zsYS-x7n9Alct1jWB3vz7kgmv5KqlY8mMK746DYZJkbDT4pRhNtxwB2CKQ0Eb=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0DQbRUNKKdyT_b8r9wOHmzfyk8qQ-5H3Oz9mJq3KJqSjAktWqvY6yIwkCc0n6t9YCMUzEOTb1hoK6wHKppqeEFh5zVXQ3lvVJ-T8mgZrMKFazysjIzR6UxtzwdoWOcADsI2Zza=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2DXDKPg1Pq7pL_-DCEXxvEAXXRPgm87GWW2SfAWw5rPKXm_3zaTbPQ6n9WmQjeOKW3gaokec8CV1xqVJZ03GI70lE4PA_b1OP3rhrn8q1b3QZk49TXvtL-lU7XzsUkYcIvfXuv=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2-2_sZ9skOZxeDR6TjmegoqjpwNogIOIJZhN21285R9NczZ1jX5PeRKXGEJjij-JDntFZMXGeRhBBEDXBZzzRGiXAxufJy6rgOQS6OMglMjGpQpzRv8OGnrqUx8heayLm_ymuA=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/AN