0zhvvP7YUHd9nPQQ=w454-h298-k-no"},{"title":"By owner","image":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/gps-cs-s/APNQkAHbzTZbZSkPDAwYXluEx7nskOCHSsjU1Cl2LZSZUJyXK8VuvmxDPxrh1dXHAVjbnF0jfbiSTIW-eYn_cDIh4HwUj54FpwMVxNTbl-HJ7QXnJhPX8WPaUaBiB6UauP8avZ_SM63KTOAWesWR=w397-h298-k-no"},{"title":"Street View \u0026 360°","image":"https://streetviewpixels-pa.googleapis.com/v1/thumbnail?panoid=hb0782_aQAEyEGlGAfxf_Q\u0026cb_client=maps_sv.tactile.gps\u0026w=224\u0026h=298\u0026yaw=164.13087\u0026pitch=0\u0026thumbfov=100"}],"reservations":null,"order_online":null,"menu":{"link":"","source":""},"owner":{"id":"109707269488495677064","name":"Blue \u0026 Blue Roofing Inc (Owner)","link":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109707269488495677064"},"complete_address":{"borough":"","street":"7814 228th St SW","city":"Edmonds","postal_code":"98026","state":"Washington","country":"US"},"about":[{"id":"service_options","name":"Service options","options":[{"name":"Onsite services","enabled":true},{"name":"Online estimates","enabled":false}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Keith C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK_A2rbszGxNOTG82lfL4qg3zgxvO5fFvno_azf5RK5LStm=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We love our Blue and Blue roof!  Everyone was professional and courteous all through the process.  Communications with the team were responded to quickly and the crew who did the installation were extremely friendly and simply amazing from set-up to clean-up.  We are very grateful for the experience and will refer Blue and Blue whenever possible.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ian F","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIKAq8lIfHk0lS9E7i3MSqX_chH-u1-Xygx-LncoKE-860OBA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I can't say enough good things about the entire team. Nobody wants to spend the money to replace a roof but if you do, might as well have it done right and have it look great. Francis was quick with the estimate and walking me through what I need, what I don't need and factors to consider. He was very responsive. Juan came out to do the project walk around and talked me through everything that I had forgotten and did a follow up after the roof was replaced, one of the nicest people to work with. And of course, Jose's team did a great job. All of my criteria was checked, they did a great job with clean up (very important) and the installation looks beautiful and is well done. The office staff and everyone else whose names I've forgotten (I apologize) were also great and easy to deal with. Can't recommend them enough.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Finnish Lutheran Church of Seattle","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJk_vKH-2fmQZF8fQ8g_FTkfwiN0CbGirxcv8pCbS1mZdDLYA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We used Blue \u0026 Blue to replace the roof on our church building. From start to finish, the project was done very professionally, on time and on budget. The project manager had good, practical suggestions for aspects of the replacement job that we didn't think of. We were left with a feeling that Blue \u0026 Blue has a true intent to provide outstanding customer service and an excellent level of craftsmanship. Everyone we interacted with was courteous and responsive. Pricing was on par with the other contractors we sought quotes from. Highly recommended.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Paul Facchini","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJls-ZsQwe8rSlGiSTH760fw4mqBsM7uU1gYh7LyVdgoXizxA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Blue \u0026 Blue Roofing did an outstanding job on my detached garage. The crew was incredibly friendly, efficient, and hardworking. They managed to complete a relatively large project in just one (long) day, and the results exceeded my expectations. I couldn’t be happier with the finished roof—highly recommend them!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Rose Hawley-Perry","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUGAUVjirtQq6vYgeNkWRWYtHm1rH-sd45-AERwKUO7Yc7WyH9B=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Was very happy with their work. They redid a section of previously poorly installed  torch down (put in by who knows, was supposed to be a brand new good when we bought the house.)\n\nThey are very knowledgeable and have a supervisor come out and check the work at the end of the job. They fix anything that person finds. I would absolutely recommend.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Brad Fuji","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIKe0JucxHZytoIcp67OCYZ6cjFBgt8KSoK0Jb2n8EKMrAtNQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Blue \u0026 Blue just completed two back-to-back jobs with replacing our two-level roof. Originally, we sought to replace the kitchen roof only since the problems seemed to be focused there.  Blue \u0026 Blue provided the most straightforward and comprehensive estimate coupled with helpful details about the specific materials to be used. The quality of their materials (triple-layer shingles, waterproof membrane, underlayment, and deck-air venting) clearly stood out. Wayde provided a helpful breakdown of their costs (which are quite reasonable) and covered areas and details that were completely overlooked by other companies' estimates. Juan and Wayde were the only ones who identified the venting problems and how they would correct it. Their crews are incredibly skilled craftsmen who take pride in their work. Knowing that one cannot assess the condition of the shiplap and joists during the estimate, Blue \u0026 Blue clearly identified the potential additional costs in case rot is discovered and replacement is required. As suspected, the work became more complicated with discovery of rotted shiplap and joists which resulted in fair additional costs. Other contractors would have jumped to balloon these costs even more than their already inflated quotes since they were not upfront about any unforeseen work and how they do their estimates. After seeing the quality of the kitchen roof replacement, we chose to have Blue \u0026 Blue replace the entire roof. Nothing but the highest praise for the quality of work completed by Anibal, Carlos, Gustavo and Octavio. Unquestionably impressed with both roof jobs, noting particularly how skillfully they crafted the shielding and underlayment around the skylights, chimney, and vent pipes like masterpieces of craftsmanship. They are proud of their tens of years of experience - kudos to Blue \u0026 Blue for retaining such skilled staff. Their warranty also shows that they stand behind their work and are trustworthy.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Deb","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKSOx2x611d1jAUgHC_LygZutXCrucCZ6brvUGY-ygdqGKklw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had Blue and Blue re-roof my flat roof in August. I am a person who likes to understand the details of a project and Blue and Blue was very willing and patient in explaining the process to me thoroughly and I am very happy with their work. I wouldn’t hesitate to use them again and have recommended them to a few friends already.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Darrell Craig","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXxphvFUZPpO0WCxCxAnKUQvW2Z_FhzQ97Nu-NcHFuSVv4eyLk=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Hired Blue \u0026 Blue to repair ridge caps on my roof. Blue \u0026 Blue was clearly the most honest and knowledgeable roofer I talked to, and their bid was extremely competitive. The work was done on time and budget and they were complete professionals end to end. We've got a full roof replacement coming up in a few years and I'll be going with Blue \u0026 Blue. In a world full of sketchy companies, especially lots of private equity owned shops with a business model built on ripping people off, it was great to work with Blue \u0026 Blue. Highly recommended!","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
