the last company I met with, and I’m glad I found them. From my initial meeting with Chase, the sales representative, to the project manager Brandon and on-site project lead Noe, every member of the team was professional and attentive.\nChase provided a thoughtful, cost-effective solution for a challenging flat roof area on my house. He took the time to clearly explain how the process would work, and the project turned out exactly as promised. The crew was not only efficient but also polite and respectful throughout the installation. I couldn’t be happier with my new roof and highly recommend Three Tree Roofing for their high-performance team and excellent results.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0Ca3fySp8J7UuCx8csMkODcnfeO-3MjkII580LAPBTac9HIidyAq92jWR6L7JEwVryFtt7dP3mnCOJNJyMQtqrGP6WN7TFGPuzIVVgF1MCVXmuMgaWeeB89n7wsrJHP7zqNtrtz0nGB7S_=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1t5fMGnsEIVq_pDmE4z9HVlW7PKFVNPcZROtb38ytl6yNyHmHjchx8BmSH59gxGeR6TzaA5laWwOorc8B8OpvZkMsGXaTgdLvdrM8x4Bg4JWrJw40kDDfyXdNUwJjuAFrqLT6LGG4ktDU=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0RN0xPV2imx9yuE2NeACWKFwjMt172SoWNxeektcnKFDMINc7B4v8khDD7lKTLwt2f3iv2W9P7bbxB_lynrhD__AkqKD36_z-TZgqqAp2IgGx_D53iDsA96oj5Yr1oklVb7eNc-w4d_fK7=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1YYAmy4IZn4mI_Cazvz2FXCyO5AHSNDv2Mk5cX4IEaojaZb1PIyLfbqP-vwrvMiya-aH8vun5KHTnQuA1Qm6EXt5CZK1d-l242KrcYbBGvqI1ym4VJKDQhi4KP-TjBAPWe53h3KREFmZdj=k-no"],"When":"2025-10-11"},{"Name":"UglyMudder","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW4jN6LtYouiSK8wsji528-sjwKINnasJfnJx1UXJef_aCoCZhD=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Just for starters, I am a renter. So I'm not the one paying the tab on this beautiful new roof that was just installed on our house. Our landlord had a number of different companies come out to do an estimate, but went with these guys. Probably the ones I would have gone with as well just from the conversations I was a part of with all the estimators. The guy from Three Tree that came out was very professional, great eye contact, nothing shady about him at all. Didn't exactly get those vibes from the others, with one exception. But this guy passed my vibe check 100%.\n\nNow, lets talk about the crew. Antonio was the foreman, great communicator. They showed up every morning at 0730 and hit the ground literally running! These 4 men busted their butts for no less than 8 hours on the first day, which was a Friday, but they had stripped all the old roofing off, installed new plywood and laid down (what used to be tar paper, it's something else now. I've not done roofing in over 30 years). Then they were very meticulous in cleaning up. Monday morning they were back at 0700, just as the roofing supply delivery truck was pulling up.  (SRS, also very professional, quick and doing their best to not leave sign of their presence) Again, worked hard all day, short lunch break, then back at it. And again, cleaning up everything to an impressive degree before heading home.\nToday, they finished up the job. Arrived 0730 and went right to it. They probably wouldn't have taken a lunch break today, but one of the vent shields was compromised, so Antonio had to go buy another one. They were completely done with the install by 1230 and spent 90 minutes going over every square inch of the perimeter of the house to make sure they got every last tiny little piece of debris from their work.\n\nI made sure they left with an ice cold 12pk, in my current situation that's the best I can do.\n\nJust from the quality of work, also not being the one paying the bill (wasn't privy to that info, also isn't really my business as a renter) I would recommend these folks to ANYONE. All I can suggest beyond that is to make sure they have access to an extension cord to plug their microwave in. They WOULD NOT come in the house, I invited them in on the first day, but felt like it was some kind of company policy or something that dictated that move so I didn't fight it. So, I did what I could do: access to power, a table to put their microwave on and a pop-up canopy over all that so everything stayed dry, even though they were working in the rain. These guys aren't used to the \"comforts\" in their workplace(s) that I am at my workplace, so I hope I helped bring some level of comfort to them. If I were in a better situation I'd have been cooking them lunch out on the grill everyday.\n\nHighly recommend, obviously. But folks, take time and thought to take care of the folks doing work for you. I feel like that's something that's long been lost in this nation. At least in this state. But, I've not forgotten. I know when I'm doing service at someone's home and they even think to offer cold water, it's great.\n\nLong enough review, but real easy compared to the level of energy I just witnessed being put into my roof.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Pam Leung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKOHrddgLjL4wELGJyAG4Mo5mNhAPlBxf63e7INjhE7BSk_bw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I hired Three Tree Roofing to replace my entire roof, and the experience was excellent from start to finish. The salesperson was very thorough and professional, providing us with a detailed quote and clearly explaining the entire process, including where the honey bucket would be placed.\n\nThe crew delivered supplies and cleaned up each day as promised, and all team members were professional and respectful. After the walkthrough, they promptly addressed and fixed any areas that needed attention. The workmanship was high-quality, and the entire project was completed in just 4.5 days.\n\nWe are very satisfied customers. While they may not be the cheapest option, the quality of their work truly speaks for itself.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Richard R","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU5zgaHTyIaoGWXWr-m4mmfKxBcFayfiwtJxBPHvqp50hRNg1mf=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"“I had a great experience with 3Tree Roofing – they were able to replace my roof and the price was very reasonable. Victor and his great were also friendly and very professional.” Showed up in a timely manner and left the jobsite clean and debris free. They answered all my questions and ensured everything was in perfect condition.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0BKfBE1mcBGDFsTs62dn4hZ8G9Msa_VkTakq2ye9qX20_eo5joi54K11I8mrzAqXHncDv9UB87t-F4MrryA_0YC70MaufHYvkg4gf0bcP_jKYcurln2TKbqzEuyszo6MON5r9LKg=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3g_wk-TwlPG4-oM8n4Xr7-nPQkZNPL4Bi8rpgQ8-9YAs-Y-nQEVrgdcGDTk8jKx8xzB1mXlzLUEsIfGfKfPSSLQpGrcmq-19xJ2crfmLmteQuItOvA5ZQD6dNhsEUw5ruuo_a4=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0WyTumF_F8KZ2Q9Pyi9DqzAaylfn_SLYSOthm9qj7H96q_Y3S0Q1TVQkyipQ7KD8nt2QGBEtOQKrqlTsQe6otf2Dt--DV4CPMsXMV3U16shKszbUOdafrVRxvf1uxj_ro3d1-s=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3bvYxx9P50th-Fi32rihrr2Ro5kNvvN9KDlonPR7xx9Q4GaFVfWogCr307l5-9jchjBHexHNwowzrC4Lx08ZesO51GrcM3vCMikRQB5uE_wEHQfOZ4yIQH8b5wQBRAEknfvGjh=k-no"],"When":"2024-6-22"},{"Name":"Mary Jo Weide","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXd178TAQnhPgjCuN4xhdKQc6JDIBPLYXb7JrvIyNiPBJCYnHc=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Three Tree Roofing did an excellent and timely job of replacing our shake roof with a metal roof.  The crew was very respectful and efficient. They were very careful of our landscaping and cleaned up every day. We decided to change the color of the gutters the morning they were coming, and they were very accommodating.  We are very pleased with our new roof.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"bruce london","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIjugl3h66AfUrMsU9bMsgnZKR1DXyhBqB-Vo_OERTzcoxz=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"working with Three Tree Roofing was an amazingly positive experience from start to finish! It's a big investment and was great to feel trusting of both the expertise and integrity of this company and their employees from start to finish. They found extensive damage on our roof that made it necessary to go above the original estimate but worked with us to keep it as low as possible. The whole crew had a such wonderful energy--they come every day so that was a welcome part of the experience:) They came on time, worked hard and were great about keeping things as clean as possible-highly recommend this company!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mark Nelson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVLokL7VjjVFsLefVie9N08aveFNHZjL622VOyf6idnseuSuU2ejw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Three Tree was great!  From the very professional and thorough quoting process, to getting the work scheduled quickly, to a great new roof at the end.  The crew was very considerate and communicative in their day to day work and they accommodated some last minute adjustments.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Vladimir Korostov","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ3mPZdmlbAVvAKV5wcJxKMAcp5nJypUbMTYEdZp9ur3-7E8Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We were referred to Three Tree Roofing by coworkers.\nTheir estimate was the most competitive among others. They offered 4 price points based on the material. No sales tactics.\nThe crew was on time every day and worked long hours. Material delivery, old roof pickup and cleaning were well organized.\nThey were straight forward with the inspection of the roof after the removal and replaced what was needed.\nShout out to Johnny's crew who did the outstanding job working steep pitch roof and keeping the site clean each day.\nWe asked to help us to fix a chronic gutter drainage issue while replacing the roof and Tree Tree Roofing accommodated our request for a reasonable price..\nWe are very satisfied with out choice.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
