"},{"title":"Roof shingle","image":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/gps-cs-s/APNQkAG8fpDZ-P3hb59RSRhKexWPZ_VBjFwCGCx45jVkYsjTasaMfLUP025b7darUQ0tblfOl-Bi_aMlFwj37XzoUVJyOzqSp5o1t_qZe6nZFEZ8pMNhQnL_0aruBw730mk2jsh5y_D-=w397-h298-k-no"},{"title":"By owner","image":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/gps-cs-s/APNQkAEnIJGP9hr6U4RIpDf73_BNYvkEz9qzHBpTyjUnrdckKCAk-B-YHq4TuQVlWZVZ8re0AGDynaKpXnoQEkNQy3flMaFrsBlAvS4CbdYgDBVuX_ezusuZea-XrBEWu0HHIobWx9c0=w397-h298-k-no"},{"title":"Street View \u0026 360°","image":"https://streetviewpixels-pa.googleapis.com/v1/thumbnail?panoid=m3gjgRvRZuY83ndwdCsXzQ\u0026cb_client=maps_sv.tactile.gps\u0026w=224\u0026h=298\u0026yaw=138.91927\u0026pitch=0\u0026thumbfov=100"}],"reservations":null,"order_online":[{"link":"http://redmondroofing.com/contact.asp","source":"redmondroofing.com"}],"menu":{"link":"","source":""},"owner":{"id":"105998491508985244448","name":"Redmond Roofing (Owner)","link":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105998491508985244448"},"complete_address":{"borough":"Southeast Redmond","street":"19205 NE Union Hill Rd","city":"Redmond","postal_code":"98053","state":"Washington","country":"US"},"about":[{"id":"accessibility","name":"Accessibility","options":[{"name":"Wheelchair accessible entrance","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible parking lot","enabled":true}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Megan LaFever","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKHksoZviOeYKKdtof8T80QpCKrENX5MU1VnkZas-JjmQswzg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Cannot recommend them enough!\nBought our house in the summer and knew if needed some work, but when rainy season came around and it started leaking into the attic, we needed to get roofers quick. After several inspections, some that never actually got quotes back to us after inspecting the roof, Redmond Roofing was highly competitive and answered all our questions.\nFrom our research, the Malarkey shingles they use are the best kind of shingle around. Don't let other companies try to tell you Owen shingles are good, they are incentived to sell that shingle. Redmond Roofing gave us quality in a fantastic price and didn't try to sway us into a bad deal like other companies.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"john godfrey","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIFcpbWJMRKEK9JUn54b9M7hMUL2y-UNvOPA5mGVeZdsWmHng=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I don’t leave many reviews, but I need to leave one for Redmond Roofing. Their support as we looked at different options was wonderful - they were very knowledgeable about the pros and cons of the companies and materials we were looking at and quickly got us samples. The pricing was very competitive. We had a roof leak a couple of weeks before the new roof was going on, and they had guys on site to have a temp fix within a couple of hours. The installation went smoothly and they avoided damaging any plants close to the house, finished on time and did a great job of cleaning. They made the whole process smooth and enjoyable, which I never would have expected for a conversion from shale to composite. I found out that they even help in the community with some families in need. These guys are great from top to bottom.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jordan S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUHcWR721s2i5dA2o25c5cEUicd5WD4-QwFGmaYdvZv9LZgYT7m=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very happy with Redmond Roofing! They had installed our roof for a previous owner, have always been very responsive and we sprung a small leak during the freeze recently. Bob had me send a quick email to confirm our address and we had a roof tech out the very next day, showed us pictures and took care of things very quickly! Super appreciative of them getting out to our home so quickly during the rainy season.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kim Klingenberg","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWYkDuYj-kLBT2kmy0PvNMXr1-rI7LffZ8LV6wA4H6cwKQLqEKM=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This review is long over-due!  If you're in need of a new roof, Redmond Roofing is the one to call!  We replaced our roof last summer and after getting 4-5 bids, we found Redmond Roofing to be straight forward with their estimate and with NO hidden costs.  Dale hand delivered the estimate, which was very easy to read and understand and he took the time to answer a few of my initial questions.  The workmanship of the crew was very professional and their daily clean up was exceptional!  They were courteous, reliable and very responsive when an issue arose.  They not only addressed it immediately, but kept us informed along the way, as our approval was needed.  Bob, the owner, was not only easy to reach with questions or concerns but stopped by periodically to check on the progress.  He is very personable and it is obvious he cares that his customers are provided top-notch service.  His employees have been with him for many years, which is a testament to what kind of an employer Bob/Redmond Roofing is.  I highly recommend Redmond Roofing for all your roofing needs.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"James N","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJn97738qFOAPkP5-v24t4zoRS9j-aOGhreJMtazcOhhC3LoQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"First as I solicited repair estimates, many roofing companies declined, new roof installations only; which seems short sighted to me. One company that seemed professional never submitted an estimate after a site visit.  The main reason I chose Redmond Roofing was the repair technician, Ricardo.  First, he performed the estimate site visit;  he seemed diligent, personable  \u0026 knowledgeable during estimate visit.   Later when I was discussing the estimate with Redmond Roofing \u0026 I asked if Ricardo would be present during the repairs.   Yes, he would be doing the repairs.  I liked the continuity.  The repair work was scheduled for 2 weeks later.  Arrived on time, worked non-stop, cleaned up and shared photos.   Another detail I appreciated: some roof plywood had to be replaced.  Ricardo showed me removed painted plywood \u0026 what it would like if not painted.  My wife \u0026 I hustled down to a paint store \u0026 purchased some can spray paint.  Those repairs blend in thanks to his shared tip.  No deposit or pre-payment required, signed an agreement \u0026 the invoice was emailed to me.\nIf I have future roofing problems this is the company would contact.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"David Semach","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIVu2z7FtnyUfXxRee9KY70z--EsqtElhkJ737wuH6jQpbpoQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I heard about Redmond Roofing via my long time contractor after I thought I had locked in on another roofing company but gave RR a shot at my business. I'm very glad I did, I found them to be very straight forward with their estimate and supporting documents to help you make an informed decision. Also, when work began the rains crept in and team left for the day and later that night around one of my many skylights we had a very slow leak which was near my TV \u0026 entertainment center- I notified Bob the owner via text and he has his crew there to fully tarp the skylights within the hour if not sooner. This was our only small issue otherwise all went as planned, team did a complete cleanup of my house and surrounding area and are very professional. Lastly Redmond Roofing has the best pricing utilizing top materials from local companies. We are very happy with the end results and hope this will be our first and last major roofing project :-)","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Erika Menninger","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJT_YzIjn3s8QnuzSjfOchlQOy6tDRk4SLyZB5Tbt7BHC_cgQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wow!  I am absolutely blown away by this company.  Redmond Roofing went out of their way to give our family a first class experience.  As a first time home buyer, we are new to home projects.  We recently bought a fixer-upper home with the roof needing quite a bit of TLC.  I reached out to this company and by the next day they had a full report, including drone photos, and tips of how we can help rehab our roof and extend the life of our current situation. This is a family business and it feels so good to work with people who are experts in this field, and pillars of our community.  Redmond Roofing is second to none and I would without a doubt recommend them to anyone looking for roofing services.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Douglas Free","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKnDNYFt8vUC9KjB7eQ3BYnj58AoN3E7CWjcZfIegk7U_YtMQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Companies often tout their ability to “exceed customer expectations”, but rarely do.  I found a true gem when I found Bob and his company Redmond Roofing.  From start to finish he and his team did a truly outstanding job and really did exceed my expectations.  His crew was thorough and detailed in their work, friendly to my family and pets, and – this may seem a little silly – did an amazing clean job cleaning up (my yard and patio were even cleaner than before!).  I simply cannot say enough nice things about the work Redmond Roofing performed.  I highly recommend them.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
