 and the quality and timing of the work.  Highly recommended.  Pete, Eric, Ivan, Evan and 'The Machine' were all great to work with.  Give them a call.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3g2sG-SLHkeOT_C11XwjPZ32S5wOq9VygmfEsM6oUCmx7TGUyzsXAardyA8T6XmZ6TVpMC3CWsAe6SDdVqq2tf1S5heuSWIVOXC16fQgI-n4HmN4aR80pJQ6U3rjv1OciMUuwLpEYlU-vS=k-no"],"When":"2026-1-31"},{"Name":"DAVE H","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL0AyeHbuwEi50Fw-VPEnvGyXgJZyQBnb4L7LHy-YFzR_Napw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"ORCA!!!!!! (2 reviews in 1.)\nAfter 26 yrs my parents house needed a new roof. I had 5 different contractors come out for an estimate. Orca was NOT the cheapest option nor the most expensive option, they ended up being middle of the road. I decided to go with them because Chris was VERY THOROUGH and explained EVERYTHING to me.\nThe crew came out and knocked it out of the park, literally took them 2.5 days and it was done. This was back in June 2025, we are currently in the heart of winter and have had some serious rainy days and EVERYTHING's been GREAT, NO LEAKS, NO ISSUES!\nFast forward to February 2026, I was so impressed by their service and workmanship I called them when the roof at my own house started to leak. (The leak was because of age but the shotty workmanship from our builder Connor Homes.) I spoke to Chris again and he set me up with Peter. Peter and crew came out and temporarily covered my roof until they are able to get me in the books.\nPeter and crew came back in about a week and took care of my roof. The entire process took about 2 days and literally 3 days after they were done we had a crazy rain storm. Once again, NO LEAKS, NO ISSUES. Orca Roofing is 2 for 2 with me, priced right and took care of my roof issues. There are not too many trustworthy businesses these days but I can honestly vouch for these guys. Thank you for taking care of my roof issues and now I can actually sleep at night.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1348ka1rrV24ztg-uieEpEFQSMV_PMV_eq3OOZRZeP1WEUhsJBtz_twN_9SynNyomoFQQD1w0YTd7L14cob9ZCKbfFCzmpHepAJ6Jht8-nAjzmyPLQNkK8HJWwuM11lmhgkibog3y82DJe=k-no"],"When":"2026-2-21"},{"Name":"Kathy Kannenberg","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocISuqxUfMwHm4LAPLQqupx8D9GKofWArNNPeH4X2xAG7l8WpQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had a great experience with Orca Roofing from start to finish. Peter was excellent at explaining the process, sometimes several times! The price was very competitive and they were also willing to do some repairs on our chimney. Eric managed most of the daily process and communicated timely and clearly. Both Peter and Eric were great representatives of Orca Roofing. Thanks so much!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Christine King","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJAkwCRdoEVq3AsT1FtuKhIq7ydlmEt6aDa_zpQGDxw1Et_Ag=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I was drawn to Orca Roofing from all the positive online reviews as my previous experience with roofing companies was not always positive. Orca blew me away. Very friendly, very communicative and made me feel like they cared about my house and made me feel comfortable with the process at every step. We ran into issues trying to re-roof my shed and pump house and Eric was on my side every step of the way coming up with creative ways to get the project done within my budget and on time. Phaedra executed the job beautifully and those 2 roofs look better than I ever imagined how they could look. They are very much deserving here in another glowing reviews.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"James Gaskin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLbvXSPxKUEDzhLXP6WDBjshh0GtsRD_0Q-lqrtho-OFfX2Lw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had to get part of our deck reinforced so that we could have a 1500 pound sauna sit on it for the duration. Paul was very patient with us as we had to delay the project, but when it was time, he was readily available. He was outstanding to work with, and his team was very professional, always showed up on time, and kept me updated regarding the project. Definitely recommend for all things related to deck repair and installation! Thanks Paul!","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn350MWFLHplUOf5K7Dkg0jbK3F6VuQnAztVwlk9JMndSZIzcBhpwUPO7pYYy0pIT1nKKejQQiC4e789xvcT5nUk5oAwlNofFbS2yoSkMVpDcQHV_mPqyl00kv30QoKbz5-C7IWTqTv8RM_A=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0hhTF5NW0Buz0BsP5-qNcRAne_aaoKOGYNEdsuasPf9EDetoesCLIIGXKIXSmkvn2HYOb3w0Ew3Gppb3ixK7HPheBLCPlv0b1A58JkadofVy6J6jaxmJpWc1Wh0I8PigYVBJd2szUsFVCu=k-no"],"When":"2025-9-8"},{"Name":"Yuri L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKk3J04sthpFuo9kVNtCKvhQjV7RS_c2LSkZ5q4USUIw4-CQ7M=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"uhmm, the pictures will tell you my experience with them.\nThey provided three repair attempts. The water leak becames more severe than when it started. 🙂\n\nFirst attempt: A plastic diverter with its head extending beyond the gutter edge. And shingles were cut and later covered with flashing. I was able to notice it after two days — during a November storm 🌧️.\n\nSecond attempt: Damaged shingles were replaced. A new kickout flashing was installed on top of the existing one. Replaced plastic diverter with aluminum downspout. The water leak continued and became more noticeable.💧\n\nLast attempt: Sealant was applied to possible leak points.\n\nResult\nWe decided to stop this game and paid full invoice. Thanks for your labor service.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn36Efq6JEhQMQCGFWPv04-EnWPf1qh2lYF-8oWZ92Rcyqui_2D3pqXo9HFLZZ06n-a5Xe1xYCNzl0I-8Bs-2dT_5JToXOnaAysydQEnPQCHRh2gfNeph5TV6w7OsWHZZhhMsH1qGvGrwg0f=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3KDW1dRJ52d1JcuoMoQGDakomtRRk-y2nBwCBmEyZX1IAoCwDYlXkHqg7ruhzgSstzyLDrQlI3F1aeLqo4zLG5nMx1GgiyVrdh35ca4-bQ7z0Wj27hrOuKqrW9S31EttSDHhJyzmzNqd7d=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2BgHArOIG4lWxr_9kAZdHDmKveusEGbDfG-x0iYBL9uII6o8Ty5s1eD_FUos0HxvMKaPwiR8rsegnCRqqBw6-JHYCwA9pQZsmZD5fNt3qCeM2104hxmIU6si-uaUpB3Ctms5Hqe-n7wmoh=k-no"],"When":"2026-2-14"},{"Name":"Emily Eddy","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJknlD-pGdsr0z14gGA0vzZueXZC1VJJ-5lnI33REwJBmnoUA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Orca came recommended by a neighbor who used them for repairs following the bomb cyclone. We had a leaking solar tube and had a really great experience with Eric! He was super communicative, asked great questions about our issue before arriving to ensure he showed up prepared to solve the problem, and fixed the issue on the first try. Honest and friendly service -- recommend! :)","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sean Santschi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWAvX44IQeOpRi9d_qrkjOopjsOyJZc7LLp2cseBjpPgzWUAOdO=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We recently had our roof replaced by Orca for our home in Lake Tapps, and I couldn't be happier with the results! The team was professional, efficient, did an excellent job from start to finish, and the crew was very respectable to my home, and left zero mess after the work was completed. They used high-quality materials, and the workmanship was top-notch. The project was completed on time and within budget. I highly recommend Orca for anyone needing roofing services. Thank you for a fantastic job!","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn33I6I5z447OSs5WQ7oJlDO1Ig9VBqgcUZFQKNCc95HCnFtX7Fattp1kK8WE8L7neDfmMc7RTH8KKwaifIsfbtfEgEe6EeriXJ71eb0u2M_YaGLPej7RaeCvqEiLQyDx_MVsaOn=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2C-zvkpm8XZc2GpEFKGz_ju3AkmmsHqk0KnSQGSrAX2yt3i0aMwRIilrK0cBTzfV9Jlus3li4S6ogBny9XI54npa27zq0r-Nd8zi5k3nMLGzeDkAKSltR9Ybm-AavMoa3UPP2a=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn18