ed great.  Walter and his crew came on a Friday (about 2 weeks later) and finished on Sunday.  Walter came to the door, introduced himself, and explained what they would be doing.  They did a great job, the roof looks fabulous!  The only problem is that now the gutters look terrible, so we'll be talking to Polar Bear again next year.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0F42hxP2yPWz1tMNOAbAqAqslvjD3zbobCgP_Pj9c8FuvB8_avTRA9OIXFYFMnA8_3RzI-AEblnhA8iYikd9FwhcSNcdzcieH-uUIktLgA45jUGeDbum1ltTC1u210nGC9_soLtyK6yvY0=k-no"],"When":"2026-2-11"},{"Name":"Nataliya Knopp","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKfP6nP0XIcH9CpmJwR5xQzzx0BG-Oy1wkK8NzYfUtY-cuhRA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had a great experience working with Polar Bear Roofing. Their team was professional, punctual, and communicated clearly throughout the entire project. The work was completed efficiently and the quality of the installation looks excellent. They kept the area clean and made sure everything was finished properly before leaving.\nOverall, a very smooth process and we’re very happy with the results. I would definitely recommend Polar Bear Roofing to anyone looking for reliable and high-quality roofing work.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Rick Veit","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW36Ory-DAicFVPU4oonT629lfCfM3sj_zS68_W8Z2ycxa8wnV2=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great working with Polar Bear! Every part of the process - sales, planning and install - was a great experience.  Pleasant employees, good price and a very clean and tidy install of 8 windows in our 2 story house.  Can't wait for the summer when we will finally have windows that actually open!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kathleen Acosta","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL30VvnUmgL-e6YuKIulZUBwbSm009I9GZacBY8a_tAYfIilw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I cannot reccommend Polar Bear enough. If you want quality materials and workmanship call Polar Bear. Project manager (Joe) and his crew (Corey and Marcus) did an outstanding job in replacing my roof and deck awning after a tree fell on my house. From first interaction until completion my experience with Polar Bear was the most professional I have ever had with any contractor. Joe came up with innovative solutions to the job. The attention to detail in the execution was amazing. They treated my house and property like it was their own and my wife and I as we were family.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Tim Glass","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKpqU88sZ-x9qx46Q-6nTw_SYEPFij4K8nZr5TIPmodzHcOtw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It's the company culture that makes them a great contractor!\n\nMy wife and I worked with Polar Bear Exteriors for a complete exterior remodel on our Whidbey Island home including new roof, James Hardie siding, Simonton Max Daylight windows, pumped in insulation and interior trim work around the new windows and a few other exterior projects.   They worked with and around our bathroom and deck contractors as well.\n\nWe were helped by their salesman to hone in our scope, style, color, budget,  etc.  They started construction on time with the new roof which was completed in about 2 days.  Soon after the window and siding crews started and they showed up everyday and worked until completed.   There was some problem solving that was handled efficiently and effectively.   They sent regular updates and all our questions, concerns were addressed almost immediately or within a day.\n\nOverall, the company is dialed in and every contact we had was pleasant, prompt and effective.   We were called ahead for start date, material drop off, transition to next crew, etc.  As a homeowner, our project went better then expected as we were prepared for glitches, problems, change orders but none of those happened and the project went better then we hoped for.\n\nPersonally, I have been a landscape architect for 32 plus years and I worked for one of the best (Alderwood Landscaping) which also has a great company culture so I know it when I see it.   If people are taken care of who work there, then they are incentivised to care and do good work.  Everyone I talked with has been with Polar Bear for a long time and some from the beginning which is a sign of great company culture.\n\nWe couldn't ask for more and I want to make sure everyone is credited for good communication, follow-up, workmanship, detail, etc. from beginning to end.\n\nIf I knew every name of the people who helped us, I would list them out but I don't know every person so it's best to credit the great project including roofing, windows, siding, sales, office staff, delivery drivers,  etc.\n\nThank you,\n\nTim and Kim","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2cMe70oV1xRP_Y7N2MNsXhf50vcTX6eGFeFUPIm9EVP1PCTCRl4P9B9VyMS-Y9YZ-cBTJLNd4d1NlGoMiiLI7DdJv1-TIoxD1qwsVoFomb6zSV3Pl30Q8y5VNz6k3cSBQFTC98U1RPkgfJ=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3kUDScg9CFYoq8r2QFsTQgOhbkPJCRuzSufxbfpCZUQqft8--pUtoAVbqp9R_nFS5g6OcuXKFiNtvBz7OAxe4S7_sfrrwnPBphq_CfOsYCNo_9JQ3BlPLfEF7d1RvMn6PC_jzbHdJapSw=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1QPXGlpV6F7r13sU1s7E8nrLQacP7V-5xx4Hp88Cw5tH9jC2PPRMd_7xQivvS7tA3uO6YQah-E6smPiN5dUkfswdyoikJLqiM06HwXAsNoF6gY6pQZDMx9mOgkvwIIJTY7SYEx7H5SjHo1=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2lN1XPryJUwMhW_7XBTfAXUqCN7RXH2mxT0mW7Gg8mo2wgfmcUZeXaAWvlTawEnYQmxLPuN4jY4T-2rxcQwUVmH8zVzmQCw6CQbsKzFRzL4UKpCBm_h-DJi-w7NINFTzrtQ643UK-zQJoY=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0G9FGreVVbGxCwxs0DaceLzLI6X86RLLlW3yHBEzN5YbDLvi0mZENiTVkEVgBWThuxvn2SvMDqToNgkDICtLTSyP1PCxSbGyvswhb58VQzH3Y8Lz6o7AWZ0WqY2DfXMyQ6tKq7Vn4NhKk=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1NWNtEGMglDQUHrCv_jncuSp94LMCH6aoZzERPRRiuNiS_UYLvjamTMljIbTHkOsutbfIxc-B6OHTSu1BiR-oEB0JUWqmhe1vAjfudR43