ime, and at the price that was quoted!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Rich Gaudi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX-oxo0HqDO1ErYGLfEETwSxqhHu2mVlwDL3_zjokrNc8B7ESk4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I own a 1905 Victorian in Wallingford. The roof has many angles,,,,, as in the House of the Seven Gables....\nThe roof had had numerous repairs and had never had plywood installed. This was a big undertaking.\nI obtained four estimates. Budget Roofing had the best price. They tore off several layers, put new plywood everywhere, and replaced some trim pieces that were not part of the bid. They did this in the most unobtrusive way and completed the job in only three days.\nThe house has a very large skylight that used to leak all the time.\nIn the last few days, we have had record rains in Seattle and the top floor of the house is bone dry, including the area around the skylight.\nI own four houses in Seattle and have dealt with many contractors. I think this is one of the best companies I have dealt with across the board.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Bruce Bowen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIasVMd7elofPh5avbC4hAcxel5cWsqHAGCUWLrxj56lhwiyQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great experience with Budget Roofing.  Excellent work, everything done on time at quoted price, owner of company always in contact. Roof and gutters look great!!! Highly recommend.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
