HAt5anXPzr0=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1xG2GUjuvYED_wPYJKLVH5hwYoTI2eR2jQ8DhOcD7V-vXJ5ZISUYe_LC8ddGUzV48rU8BWwEf7K58wr1PFsQuzRa8yUYCIm9W1LVqvokz8d3xvRvBIlGYPAOiPNC04yuPfG8QZ=k-no"],"When":"2024-7-16"},{"Name":"Roger Krause","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKRf3liXhDJOqq80bcVp4A1CTXCZH_QtZiLIJysCs-LYETgiA7K=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Terry Bridgman arrived at the pre-scheduled time to inspect our old roof and provided us with a detailed written bid on replacing it with high quality Malarkey roofing products. He also noted that our chimney cap was in need of replacement and provided us a bid for that work also. We figured the chimney work was due as our house is 45 years old.\nWe elected to go ahead with both these projects (roof and chimney). Both of these projects were completed with expert, efficient care.\nTiana kept us well informed via email of the project process and beginning and end dates.\nThe re-roofing team found several sheets of the old plywood that had failed due to rot. These sheets were removed and replaced with new sheets prior to the new roofing material being put down.\nBottom line is, we were very pleased with the professionalism, project management and overall outcome of this project. They did a stellar job of cleaning up the area after the work was completed. You'd never know they'd been here except for our new roof! We would highly recommend Four Seasons Roofing to anyone looking for expert roof installation.\nLastly, our neighbors had used and recommended Four Seasons after they had their roof replaced a couple of years ago. Another reason we elected to work with them.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1MwaCoWerHcseqixYMUo2ffZBDQVZAk7-EKwuHlB6Dn7TW8fn6GpAZBKM3yKJjVLIvjD4WmvOWiJSc6Oqxup22hrNynpjLBD-UJ8dsFnWAJ5XAPs5_KFtR3Q68u3lqPGfTUjut=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0RBRagJ35RfCNlmvpZsUMvBj5AX0P3ONKBQvS97ZZbFov406foVMxt